dom-audiotrack-enabled-dev.name: enabled
dom-audiotrack-enabled-dev.summary: The AudioTrack property enabled specifies whether or not the described audio track is currently enabled for use. If the track is disabled by setting enabled to false, the track is muted and does not produce audio.
dom-audiotrack-enabled-dev.title: AudioTrack: enabled property

dom-audiotrack-id-dev.name: id
dom-audiotrack-id-dev.summary: The id property contains a string which uniquely identifies the track represented by the AudioTrack.
dom-audiotrack-id-dev.title: AudioTrack: id property

dom-audiotrack-kind-dev.name: kind
dom-audiotrack-kind-dev.summary: The kind property contains a string indicating the category of audio contained in the AudioTrack.
dom-audiotrack-kind-dev.title: AudioTrack: kind property

dom-audiotrack-label-dev.name: label
dom-audiotrack-label-dev.summary: The read-only AudioTrack property label returns a string specifying the audio track's human-readable label, if one is available; otherwise, it returns an empty string.
dom-audiotrack-label-dev.title: AudioTrack: label property

dom-audiotrack-language-dev.name: language
dom-audiotrack-language-dev.summary: The read-only AudioTrack property language returns a string identifying the language used in the audio track.
dom-audiotrack-language-dev.title: AudioTrack: language property

audiotrack.name: AudioTrack
audiotrack.summary: The AudioTrack interface represents a single audio track from one of the HTML media elements, <audio> or <video>.
audiotrack.title: AudioTrack

event-media-addtrack.name: addtrack_event
event-media-addtrack.summary: The addtrack event is fired when a track is added to an AudioTrackList.
event-media-addtrack.title: AudioTrackList: addtrack event

event-media-addtrack.name: addtrack_event
event-media-addtrack.summary: The addtrack event is fired when a track is added to a TextTrackList.
event-media-addtrack.title: TextTrackList: addtrack event

event-media-addtrack.name: addtrack_event
event-media-addtrack.summary: The addtrack event is fired when a video track is added to a VideoTrackList.
event-media-addtrack.title: VideoTrackList: addtrack event

handler-tracklist-onaddtrack.name: addtrack_event
handler-tracklist-onaddtrack.summary: The addtrack event is fired when a track is added to an AudioTrackList.
handler-tracklist-onaddtrack.title: AudioTrackList: addtrack event

handler-tracklist-onaddtrack.name: addtrack_event
handler-tracklist-onaddtrack.summary: The addtrack event is fired when a track is added to a TextTrackList.
handler-tracklist-onaddtrack.title: TextTrackList: addtrack event

handler-tracklist-onaddtrack.name: addtrack_event
handler-tracklist-onaddtrack.summary: The addtrack event is fired when a video track is added to a VideoTrackList.
handler-tracklist-onaddtrack.title: VideoTrackList: addtrack event

event-media-change.name: change_event
event-media-change.summary: The change event is fired when an audio track is enabled or disabled, for example by changing the track's enabled property.
event-media-change.title: AudioTrackList: change event

event-media-change.name: change_event
event-media-change.summary: The change event is fired when a text track is made active or inactive, or a TextTrackList is otherwise changed.
event-media-change.title: TextTrackList: change event

event-media-change.name: change_event
event-media-change.summary: The change event is fired when a video track is made active or inactive, for example by changing the track's selected property.
event-media-change.title: VideoTrackList: change event

handler-tracklist-onchange.name: change_event
handler-tracklist-onchange.summary: The change event is fired when an audio track is enabled or disabled, for example by changing the track's enabled property.
handler-tracklist-onchange.title: AudioTrackList: change event

handler-tracklist-onchange.name: change_event
handler-tracklist-onchange.summary: The change event is fired when a text track is made active or inactive, or a TextTrackList is otherwise changed.
handler-tracklist-onchange.title: TextTrackList: change event

handler-tracklist-onchange.name: change_event
handler-tracklist-onchange.summary: The change event is fired when a video track is made active or inactive, for example by changing the track's selected property.
handler-tracklist-onchange.title: VideoTrackList: change event

dom-audiotracklist-gettrackbyid-dev.name: getTrackById
dom-audiotracklist-gettrackbyid-dev.summary: The AudioTrackList method getTrackById() returns the first AudioTrack object from the track list whose id matches the specified string. This lets you find a specified track if you know its ID string.
dom-audiotracklist-gettrackbyid-dev.title: AudioTrackList: getTrackById() method

dom-audiotracklist-length-dev.name: length
dom-audiotracklist-length-dev.summary: The read-only AudioTrackList property length returns the number of entries in the AudioTrackList, each of which is an AudioTrack representing one audio track in the media element. A value of 0 indicates that there are no audio tracks in the media.
dom-audiotracklist-length-dev.title: AudioTrackList: length property

event-media-removetrack.name: removetrack_event
event-media-removetrack.summary: The removetrack event is fired when a track is removed from an AudioTrackList.
event-media-removetrack.title: AudioTrackList: removetrack event

event-media-removetrack.name: removetrack_event
event-media-removetrack.summary: The removetrack event is fired when a track is removed from a TextTrackList.
event-media-removetrack.title: TextTrackList: removeTrack event

event-media-removetrack.name: removetrack_event
event-media-removetrack.summary: The removetrack event is fired when a video track is removed from a VideoTrackList.
event-media-removetrack.title: VideoTrackList: removetrack event

handler-tracklist-onremovetrack.name: removetrack_event
handler-tracklist-onremovetrack.summary: The removetrack event is fired when a track is removed from an AudioTrackList.
handler-tracklist-onremovetrack.title: AudioTrackList: removetrack event

handler-tracklist-onremovetrack.name: removetrack_event
handler-tracklist-onremovetrack.summary: The removetrack event is fired when a track is removed from a TextTrackList.
handler-tracklist-onremovetrack.title: TextTrackList: removeTrack event

handler-tracklist-onremovetrack.name: removetrack_event
handler-tracklist-onremovetrack.summary: The removetrack event is fired when a video track is removed from a VideoTrackList.
handler-tracklist-onremovetrack.title: VideoTrackList: removetrack event

audiotracklist-and-videotracklist-object.name: AudioTrackList
audiotracklist-and-videotracklist-object.summary: The AudioTrackList interface is used to represent a list of the audio tracks contained within a given HTML media element, with each track represented by a separate AudioTrack object in the list.
audiotracklist-and-videotracklist-object.title: AudioTrackList

audiotracklist-and-videotracklist-object.name: VideoTrackList
audiotracklist-and-videotracklist-object.summary: The VideoTrackList interface is used to represent a list of the video tracks contained within a <video> element, with each track represented by a separate VideoTrack object in the list.
audiotracklist-and-videotracklist-object.title: VideoTrackList

audiotracklist-and-videotracklist-object.name: AudioTrackList
audiotracklist-and-videotracklist-object.summary: The AudioTrackList interface is used to represent a list of the audio tracks contained within a given HTML media element, with each track represented by a separate AudioTrack object in the list.
audiotracklist-and-videotracklist-object.title: AudioTrackList

dom-barprop-visible.name: visible
dom-barprop-visible.summary: The visible read-only property of the BarProp interface returns true if the user interface element it represents is visible.
dom-barprop-visible.title: BarProp: visible property

barprop.name: BarProp
barprop.summary: The BarProp interface of the Document Object Model represents the web browser user interface elements that are exposed to scripts in web pages. Each of the following interface elements are represented by a BarProp object.
barprop.title: BarProp

the-beforeunloadevent-interface.name: BeforeUnloadEvent
the-beforeunloadevent-interface.summary: BeforeUnloadEvent is an interface for the beforeunload event.
the-beforeunloadevent-interface.title: BeforeUnloadEvent

dom-broadcastchannel-dev.name: BroadcastChannel
dom-broadcastchannel-dev.summary: The BroadcastChannel() constructor creates a new BroadcastChannel and connects it to the underlying channel.
dom-broadcastchannel-dev.title: BroadcastChannel: BroadcastChannel() constructor

dom-broadcastchannel-close-dev.name: close
dom-broadcastchannel-close-dev.summary: The BroadcastChannel.close() terminates the connection to the underlying channel, allowing the object to be garbage collected. This is a necessary step to perform as there is no other way for a browser to know that this channel is not needed anymore.
dom-broadcastchannel-close-dev.title: BroadcastChannel: close() method

event-message.name: message_event
event-message.summary: The message event is fired on a BroadcastChannel object when a message arrives on that channel.
event-message.title: BroadcastChannel: message event

event-message.name: message_event
event-message.summary: The message event is fired on a DedicatedWorkerGlobalScope object when the worker receives a message from its parent (i.e. when the parent sends a message using Worker.postMessage()).
event-message.title: DedicatedWorkerGlobalScope: message event

event-message.name: message_event
event-message.summary: The message event of the EventSource API is fired when data is received through an event source.
event-message.title: EventSource: message event

event-message.name: message_event
event-message.summary: The message event is fired on a MessagePort object when a message arrives on that channel.

nodejs.notes: Supports the event, but only via Node EventEmitter.

event-message.title: MessagePort: message event

event-message.name: message_event
event-message.summary: The message event is fired on a Window object when the window receives a message, for example from a call to Window.postMessage() from another browsing context.
event-message.title: Window: message event

event-message.name: message_event
event-message.summary: The message event is fired on a Worker object when the worker's parent receives a message from its worker (i.e. when the worker sends a message using DedicatedWorkerGlobalScope.postMessage()).

nodejs.notes: Supports the event, but only via Node EventEmitter.
Supports the event, but only via Node EventEmitter.
Supports the event, but only via Node EventEmitter.

event-message.title: Worker: message event

handler-broadcastchannel-onmessage.name: message_event
handler-broadcastchannel-onmessage.summary: The message event is fired on a BroadcastChannel object when a message arrives on that channel.
handler-broadcastchannel-onmessage.title: BroadcastChannel: message event

event-messageerror.name: messageerror_event
event-messageerror.summary: The messageerror event is fired on a BroadcastChannel object when a message that can't be deserialized arrives on the channel.
event-messageerror.title: BroadcastChannel: messageerror event

event-messageerror.name: messageerror_event
event-messageerror.summary: The messageerror event is fired on a DedicatedWorkerGlobalScope object when it receives a message that can't be deserialized.

safari.notes: See bug 171216.

event-messageerror.title: DedicatedWorkerGlobalScope: messageerror event

event-messageerror.name: messageerror_event
event-messageerror.summary: The messageerror event is fired on a MessagePort object when it receives a message that can't be deserialized.

nodejs.notes: Supports the event, but only via Node EventEmitter.

safari.notes: See bug 171216.

event-messageerror.title: MessagePort: messageerror event

event-messageerror.name: messageerror_event
event-messageerror.summary: The messageerror event is fired on a Window object when it receives a message that can't be deserialized.

safari.notes: See bug 171216.

event-messageerror.title: Window: messageerror event

event-messageerror.name: messageerror_event
event-messageerror.summary: The messageerror event is fired on a Worker object when it receives a message that can't be deserialized.

safari.notes: See bug 171216.

event-messageerror.title: Worker: messageerror event

handler-broadcastchannel-onmessageerror.name: messageerror_event
handler-broadcastchannel-onmessageerror.summary: The messageerror event is fired on a BroadcastChannel object when a message that can't be deserialized arrives on the channel.
handler-broadcastchannel-onmessageerror.title: BroadcastChannel: messageerror event

dom-broadcastchannel-name-dev.name: name
dom-broadcastchannel-name-dev.summary: The read-only BroadcastChannel.name property returns a string, which uniquely identifies the given channel with its name. This name is passed to the BroadcastChannel() constructor at creation time and is therefore read-only.
dom-broadcastchannel-name-dev.title: BroadcastChannel: name property

dom-broadcastchannel-postmessage-dev.name: postMessage
dom-broadcastchannel-postmessage-dev.summary: The BroadcastChannel.postMessage() sends a message, which can be of any kind of Object, to each listener in any browsing context with the same origin. The message is transmitted as a 'message' event targeted at each BroadcastChannel bound to the channel.
dom-broadcastchannel-postmessage-dev.title: BroadcastChannel: postMessage() method

broadcasting-to-other-browsing-contexts.name: BroadcastChannel
broadcasting-to-other-browsing-contexts.summary: The BroadcastChannel interface represents a named channel that any browsing context of a given origin can subscribe to. It allows communication between different documents (in different windows, tabs, frames or iframes) of the same origin. Messages are broadcasted via a message event fired at all BroadcastChannel objects listening to the channel, except the object that sent the message.

notes: Experimental implementation
Must be imported using either require('worker_threads') or import * from 'worker_threads'.

broadcasting-to-other-browsing-contexts.title: BroadcastChannel

broadcasting-to-other-browsing-contexts.name: Broadcast_Channel_API
broadcasting-to-other-browsing-contexts.summary: The Broadcast Channel API allows basic communication between browsing contexts (that is, windows, tabs, frames, or iframes) and workers on the same origin.

notes: Experimental implementation
Must be imported using either require('worker_threads') or import * from 'worker_threads'.

broadcasting-to-other-browsing-contexts.title: Broadcast Channel API

dom-canvasgradient-addcolorstop-dev.name: addColorStop
dom-canvasgradient-addcolorstop-dev.summary: The CanvasGradient.addColorStop() method adds a new color stop, defined by an offset and a color, to a given canvas gradient.
dom-canvasgradient-addcolorstop-dev.title: CanvasGradient: addColorStop() method

canvasgradient.name: CanvasGradient
canvasgradient.summary: The CanvasGradient interface represents an opaque object describing a gradient. It is returned by the methods CanvasRenderingContext2D.createLinearGradient(), CanvasRenderingContext2D.createConicGradient() or CanvasRenderingContext2D.createRadialGradient().

firefox.notes: Before Firefox 5.0, specifying non-finite values when adding color stops through a call to addColorStop() incorrectly throws SYNTAX_ERR instead of INDEX_SIZE_ERR.

canvasgradient.title: CanvasGradient

dom-canvaspattern-settransform-dev.name: setTransform
dom-canvaspattern-settransform-dev.summary: The CanvasPattern.setTransform() method uses a DOMMatrix object as the pattern's transformation matrix and invokes it on the pattern.
dom-canvaspattern-settransform-dev.title: CanvasPattern: setTransform() method

canvaspattern.name: CanvasPattern
canvaspattern.summary: The CanvasPattern interface represents an opaque object describing a pattern, based on an image, a canvas, or a video, created by the CanvasRenderingContext2D.createPattern() method.
canvaspattern.title: CanvasPattern

dom-context-2d-arc-dev.name: arc
dom-context-2d-arc-dev.summary: The CanvasRenderingContext2D.arc() method of the Canvas 2D API adds a circular arc to the current sub-path.
dom-context-2d-arc-dev.title: CanvasRenderingContext2D: arc() method

dom-context-2d-arcto-dev.name: arcTo
dom-context-2d-arcto-dev.summary: The CanvasRenderingContext2D.arcTo() method of the Canvas 2D API adds a circular arc to the current sub-path, using the given control points and radius. The arc is automatically connected to the path's latest point with a straight line, if necessary for the specified parameters.
dom-context-2d-arcto-dev.title: CanvasRenderingContext2D: arcTo() method

dom-context-2d-beginpath-dev.name: beginPath
dom-context-2d-beginpath-dev.summary: The CanvasRenderingContext2D.beginPath() method of the Canvas 2D API starts a new path by emptying the list of sub-paths. Call this method when you want to create a new path.
dom-context-2d-beginpath-dev.title: CanvasRenderingContext2D: beginPath() method

dom-context-2d-beziercurveto-dev.name: bezierCurveTo
dom-context-2d-beziercurveto-dev.summary: The CanvasRenderingContext2D.bezierCurveTo() method of the Canvas 2D API adds a cubic Bzier curve to the current sub-path. It requires three points: the first two are control points and the third one is the end point. The starting point is the latest point in the current path, which can be changed using moveTo() before creating the Bzier curve.
dom-context-2d-beziercurveto-dev.title: CanvasRenderingContext2D: bezierCurveTo() method

dom-context-2d-canvas-dev.name: canvas
dom-context-2d-canvas-dev.summary: The CanvasRenderingContext2D.canvas property, part of the Canvas API, is a read-only reference to the HTMLCanvasElement object that is associated with a given context. It might be null if there is no associated <canvas> element.
dom-context-2d-canvas-dev.title: CanvasRenderingContext2D: canvas property

dom-context-2d-clearrect-dev.name: clearRect
dom-context-2d-clearrect-dev.summary: The CanvasRenderingContext2D.clearRect() method of the Canvas 2D API erases the pixels in a rectangular area by setting them to transparent black.
dom-context-2d-clearrect-dev.title: CanvasRenderingContext2D: clearRect() method

dom-context-2d-clip-dev.name: clip
dom-context-2d-clip-dev.summary: The CanvasRenderingContext2D.clip() method of the Canvas 2D API turns the current or given path into the current clipping region. The previous clipping region, if any, is intersected with the current or given path to create the new clipping region.
dom-context-2d-clip-dev.title: CanvasRenderingContext2D: clip() method

dom-context-2d-closepath-dev.name: closePath
dom-context-2d-closepath-dev.summary: The CanvasRenderingContext2D.closePath() method of the Canvas 2D API attempts to add a straight line from the current point to the start of the current sub-path. If the shape has already been closed or has only one point, this function does nothing.
dom-context-2d-closepath-dev.title: CanvasRenderingContext2D: closePath() method

dom-context-2d-createconicgradient-dev.name: createConicGradient
dom-context-2d-createconicgradient-dev.summary: The CanvasRenderingContext2D.createConicGradient() method of the Canvas 2D API creates a gradient around a point with given coordinates.

firefox.notes: Implements an older version of the specification. The gradient starts from a line going vertically up from the center, like the equivalent CSS function.

safari.notes: Implements an older version of the specification. The gradient starts from a line going vertically up from the center, like the equivalent CSS function.

dom-context-2d-createconicgradient-dev.title: CanvasRenderingContext2D: createConicGradient() method

dom-context-2d-createimagedata-dev.name: createImageData
dom-context-2d-createimagedata-dev.summary: The CanvasRenderingContext2D.createImageData() method of the Canvas 2D API creates a new, blank ImageData object with the specified dimensions. All of the pixels in the new object are transparent black.
dom-context-2d-createimagedata-dev.title: CanvasRenderingContext2D: createImageData() method

dom-context-2d-createlineargradient-dev.name: createLinearGradient
dom-context-2d-createlineargradient-dev.summary: The CanvasRenderingContext2D.createLinearGradient() method of the Canvas 2D API creates a gradient along the line connecting two given coordinates.
dom-context-2d-createlineargradient-dev.title: CanvasRenderingContext2D: createLinearGradient() method

dom-context-2d-createpattern-dev.name: createPattern
dom-context-2d-createpattern-dev.summary: The CanvasRenderingContext2D.createPattern() method of the Canvas 2D API creates a pattern using the specified image and repetition. This method returns a CanvasPattern.
dom-context-2d-createpattern-dev.title: CanvasRenderingContext2D: createPattern() method

dom-context-2d-createradialgradient-dev.name: createRadialGradient
dom-context-2d-createradialgradient-dev.summary: The CanvasRenderingContext2D.createRadialGradient() method of the Canvas 2D API creates a radial gradient using the size and coordinates of two circles.
dom-context-2d-createradialgradient-dev.title: CanvasRenderingContext2D: createRadialGradient() method

dom-context-2d-direction-dev.name: direction
dom-context-2d-direction-dev.summary: The CanvasRenderingContext2D.direction property of the Canvas 2D API specifies the current text direction used to draw text.
dom-context-2d-direction-dev.title: CanvasRenderingContext2D: direction property

dom-context-2d-drawfocusifneeded-dev.name: drawFocusIfNeeded
dom-context-2d-drawfocusifneeded-dev.summary: The CanvasRenderingContext2D.drawFocusIfNeeded() method of the Canvas 2D API draws a focus ring around the current or given path, if the specified element is focused.
dom-context-2d-drawfocusifneeded-dev.title: CanvasRenderingContext2D: drawFocusIfNeeded() method

dom-context-2d-drawimage-dev.name: drawImage
dom-context-2d-drawimage-dev.summary: The CanvasRenderingContext2D.drawImage() method of the Canvas 2D API provides different ways to draw an image onto the canvas.
dom-context-2d-drawimage-dev.title: CanvasRenderingContext2D: drawImage() method

dom-context-2d-ellipse-dev.name: ellipse
dom-context-2d-ellipse-dev.summary: The CanvasRenderingContext2D.ellipse() method of the Canvas 2D API adds an elliptical arc to the current sub-path.
dom-context-2d-ellipse-dev.title: CanvasRenderingContext2D: ellipse() method

dom-context-2d-fill-dev.name: fill
dom-context-2d-fill-dev.summary: The CanvasRenderingContext2D.fill() method of the Canvas 2D API fills the current or given path with the current fillStyle.
dom-context-2d-fill-dev.title: CanvasRenderingContext2D: fill() method

dom-context-2d-fillrect-dev.name: fillRect
dom-context-2d-fillrect-dev.summary: The CanvasRenderingContext2D.fillRect() method of the Canvas 2D API draws a rectangle that is filled according to the current fillStyle.
dom-context-2d-fillrect-dev.title: CanvasRenderingContext2D: fillRect() method

dom-context-2d-fillstyle-dev.name: fillStyle
dom-context-2d-fillstyle-dev.summary: The CanvasRenderingContext2D.fillStyle property of the Canvas 2D API specifies the color, gradient, or pattern to use inside shapes. The default style is #000 (black).
dom-context-2d-fillstyle-dev.title: CanvasRenderingContext2D: fillStyle property

dom-context-2d-filltext-dev.name: fillText
dom-context-2d-filltext-dev.summary: The CanvasRenderingContext2D method fillText(), part of the Canvas 2D API, draws a text string at the specified coordinates, filling the string's characters with the current fillStyle. An optional parameter allows specifying a maximum width for the rendered text, which the user agent will achieve by condensing the text or by using a lower font size.
dom-context-2d-filltext-dev.title: CanvasRenderingContext2D: fillText() method

dom-context-2d-filter-dev.name: filter
dom-context-2d-filter-dev.summary: The CanvasRenderingContext2D.filter property of the Canvas 2D API provides filter effects such as blurring and grayscaling. It is similar to the CSS filter property and accepts the same values.

safari.notes: See bug 198416.

dom-context-2d-filter-dev.title: CanvasRenderingContext2D: filter property

dom-context-2d-font-dev.name: font
dom-context-2d-font-dev.summary: The CanvasRenderingContext2D.font property of the Canvas 2D API specifies the current text style to use when drawing text. This string uses the same syntax as the CSS font specifier.
dom-context-2d-font-dev.title: CanvasRenderingContext2D: font property

dom-context-2d-fontkerning.name: fontKerning
dom-context-2d-fontkerning.summary: The CanvasRenderingContext2D.fontKerning property of the Canvas API specifies how font kerning information is used.
dom-context-2d-fontkerning.title: CanvasRenderingContext2D: fontKerning property

dom-context-2d-fontstretch.name: fontStretch
dom-context-2d-fontstretch.summary: The CanvasRenderingContext2D.fontStretch property of the Canvas API specifies how the font may be expanded or condensed when drawing text.
dom-context-2d-fontstretch.title: CanvasRenderingContext2D: fontStretch property

dom-context-2d-fontvariantcaps.name: fontVariantCaps
dom-context-2d-fontvariantcaps.summary: The CanvasRenderingContext2D.fontVariantCaps property of the Canvas API specifies an alternative capitalization of the rendered text.
dom-context-2d-fontvariantcaps.title: CanvasRenderingContext2D: fontVariantCaps property

2dcontext:dom-context-2d-canvas-getconte.name: getContextAttributes
2dcontext:dom-context-2d-canvas-getconte.summary: The CanvasRenderingContext2D.getContextAttributes() method returns an object that contains the actual context parameters. Context attributes can be requested with HTMLCanvasElement.getContext() on context creation.
2dcontext:dom-context-2d-canvas-getconte.title: CanvasRenderingContext2D: getContextAttributes() method

dom-context-2d-getimagedata-dev.name: getImageData
dom-context-2d-getimagedata-dev.summary: The CanvasRenderingContext2D method getImageData() of the Canvas 2D API returns an ImageData object representing the underlying pixel data for a specified portion of the canvas.

firefox.notes: Since Firefox 5, getImageData now correctly accepts rectangles that extend beyond the bounds of the canvas; pixels outside the canvas are returned as transparent black and now also returns at least one pixel's worth of image data if a rectangle smaller than one pixel is specified.

dom-context-2d-getimagedata-dev.title: CanvasRenderingContext2D: getImageData() method

dom-context-2d-getlinedash-dev.name: getLineDash
dom-context-2d-getlinedash-dev.summary: The getLineDash() method of the Canvas 2D API's CanvasRenderingContext2D interface gets the current line dash pattern.
dom-context-2d-getlinedash-dev.title: CanvasRenderingContext2D: getLineDash() method

dom-context-2d-gettransform-dev.name: getTransform
dom-context-2d-gettransform-dev.summary: The CanvasRenderingContext2D.getTransform() method of the Canvas 2D API retrieves the current transformation matrix being applied to the context.
dom-context-2d-gettransform-dev.title: CanvasRenderingContext2D: getTransform() method

dom-context-2d-globalalpha-dev.name: globalAlpha
dom-context-2d-globalalpha-dev.summary: The CanvasRenderingContext2D.globalAlpha property of the Canvas 2D API specifies the alpha (transparency) value that is applied to shapes and images before they are drawn onto the canvas.
dom-context-2d-globalalpha-dev.title: CanvasRenderingContext2D: globalAlpha property

dom-context-2d-globalcompositeoperation-.name: globalCompositeOperation
dom-context-2d-globalcompositeoperation-.summary: The CanvasRenderingContext2D.globalCompositeOperation property of the Canvas 2D API sets the type of compositing operation to apply when drawing new shapes.
dom-context-2d-globalcompositeoperation-.title: CanvasRenderingContext2D: globalCompositeOperation property

dom-context-2d-imagesmoothingenabled-dev.name: imageSmoothingEnabled
dom-context-2d-imagesmoothingenabled-dev.summary: The imageSmoothingEnabled property of the CanvasRenderingContext2D interface, part of the Canvas API, determines whether scaled images are smoothed (true, default) or not (false). On getting the imageSmoothingEnabled property, the last value it was set to is returned.
dom-context-2d-imagesmoothingenabled-dev.title: CanvasRenderingContext2D: imageSmoothingEnabled property

dom-context-2d-imagesmoothingquality-dev.name: imageSmoothingQuality
dom-context-2d-imagesmoothingquality-dev.summary: The imageSmoothingQuality property of the CanvasRenderingContext2D interface, part of the Canvas API, lets you set the quality of image smoothing.
dom-context-2d-imagesmoothingquality-dev.title: CanvasRenderingContext2D: imageSmoothingQuality property

dom-context-2d-iscontextlost.name: isContextLost
dom-context-2d-iscontextlost.summary: The CanvasRenderingContext2D.isContextLost() method of the Canvas 2D API returns true if the rendering context is lost (and has not yet been reset). This might occur due to driver crashes, running out of memory, and so on.
dom-context-2d-iscontextlost.title: CanvasRenderingContext2D: isContextLost() method

dom-context-2d-ispointinpath-dev.name: isPointInPath
dom-context-2d-ispointinpath-dev.summary: The CanvasRenderingContext2D.isPointInPath() method of the Canvas 2D API reports whether or not the specified point is contained in the current path.
dom-context-2d-ispointinpath-dev.title: CanvasRenderingContext2D: isPointInPath() method

dom-context-2d-ispointinstroke-dev.name: isPointInStroke
dom-context-2d-ispointinstroke-dev.summary: The CanvasRenderingContext2D.isPointInStroke() method of the Canvas 2D API reports whether or not the specified point is inside the area contained by the stroking of a path.
dom-context-2d-ispointinstroke-dev.title: CanvasRenderingContext2D: isPointInStroke() method

dom-context-2d-letterspacing.name: letterSpacing
dom-context-2d-letterspacing.summary: The CanvasRenderingContext2D.letterSpacing property of the Canvas API specifies the spacing between letters when drawing text.
dom-context-2d-letterspacing.title: CanvasRenderingContext2D: letterSpacing property

dom-context-2d-linecap-dev.name: lineCap
dom-context-2d-linecap-dev.summary: The CanvasRenderingContext2D.lineCap property of the Canvas 2D API determines the shape used to draw the end points of lines.
dom-context-2d-linecap-dev.title: CanvasRenderingContext2D: lineCap property

dom-context-2d-linedashoffset-dev.name: lineDashOffset
dom-context-2d-linedashoffset-dev.summary: The CanvasRenderingContext2D.lineDashOffset property of the Canvas 2D API sets the line dash offset, or "phase."
dom-context-2d-linedashoffset-dev.title: CanvasRenderingContext2D: lineDashOffset property

dom-context-2d-linejoin-dev.name: lineJoin
dom-context-2d-linejoin-dev.summary: The CanvasRenderingContext2D.lineJoin property of the Canvas 2D API determines the shape used to join two line segments where they meet.
dom-context-2d-linejoin-dev.title: CanvasRenderingContext2D: lineJoin property

dom-context-2d-lineto-dev.name: lineTo
dom-context-2d-lineto-dev.summary: The CanvasRenderingContext2D method lineTo(), part of the Canvas 2D API, adds a straight line to the current sub-path by connecting the sub-path's last point to the specified (x, y) coordinates.
dom-context-2d-lineto-dev.title: CanvasRenderingContext2D: lineTo() method

dom-context-2d-linewidth-dev.name: lineWidth
dom-context-2d-linewidth-dev.summary: The CanvasRenderingContext2D.lineWidth property of the Canvas 2D API sets the thickness of lines.
dom-context-2d-linewidth-dev.title: CanvasRenderingContext2D: lineWidth property

dom-context-2d-measuretext-dev.name: measureText
dom-context-2d-measuretext-dev.summary: The CanvasRenderingContext2D.measureText() method returns a TextMetrics object that contains information about the measured text (such as its width, for example).
dom-context-2d-measuretext-dev.title: CanvasRenderingContext2D: measureText() method

dom-context-2d-miterlimit-dev.name: miterLimit
dom-context-2d-miterlimit-dev.summary: The CanvasRenderingContext2D.miterLimit property of the Canvas 2D API sets the miter limit ratio.
dom-context-2d-miterlimit-dev.title: CanvasRenderingContext2D: miterLimit property

dom-context-2d-moveto-dev.name: moveTo
dom-context-2d-moveto-dev.summary: The CanvasRenderingContext2D.moveTo() method of the Canvas 2D API begins a new sub-path at the point specified by the given (x, y) coordinates.
dom-context-2d-moveto-dev.title: CanvasRenderingContext2D: moveTo() method

dom-context-2d-putimagedata-dev.name: putImageData
dom-context-2d-putimagedata-dev.summary: The CanvasRenderingContext2D.putImageData() method of the Canvas 2D API paints data from the given ImageData object onto the canvas. If a dirty rectangle is provided, only the pixels from that rectangle are painted. This method is not affected by the canvas transformation matrix.
dom-context-2d-putimagedata-dev.title: CanvasRenderingContext2D: putImageData() method

dom-context-2d-quadraticcurveto-dev.name: quadraticCurveTo
dom-context-2d-quadraticcurveto-dev.summary: The CanvasRenderingContext2D.quadraticCurveTo() method of the Canvas 2D API adds a quadratic Bzier curve to the current sub-path. It requires two points: the first one is a control point and the second one is the end point. The starting point is the latest point in the current path, which can be changed using moveTo() before creating the quadratic Bzier curve.
dom-context-2d-quadraticcurveto-dev.title: CanvasRenderingContext2D: quadraticCurveTo() method

dom-context-2d-rect-dev.name: rect
dom-context-2d-rect-dev.summary: The CanvasRenderingContext2D.rect() method of the Canvas 2D API adds a rectangle to the current path.
dom-context-2d-rect-dev.title: CanvasRenderingContext2D: rect() method

dom-context-2d-reset.name: reset
dom-context-2d-reset.summary: The CanvasRenderingContext2D.reset() method of the Canvas 2D API resets the rendering context to its default state, allowing it to be reused for drawing something else without having to explicitly reset all the properties.
dom-context-2d-reset.title: CanvasRenderingContext2D: reset() method

dom-context-2d-reset.name: reset
dom-context-2d-reset.summary: The OffscreenCanvasRenderingContext2D interface is a CanvasRenderingContext2D rendering context for drawing to the bitmap of an OffscreenCanvas object. It is similar to the CanvasRenderingContext2D object, with the following differences:
dom-context-2d-reset.title: OffscreenCanvasRenderingContext2D

dom-context-2d-resettransform-dev.name: resetTransform
dom-context-2d-resettransform-dev.summary: The CanvasRenderingContext2D.resetTransform() method of the Canvas 2D API resets the current transform to the identity matrix.
dom-context-2d-resettransform-dev.title: CanvasRenderingContext2D: resetTransform() method

dom-context-2d-restore-dev.name: restore
dom-context-2d-restore-dev.summary: The CanvasRenderingContext2D.restore() method of the Canvas 2D API restores the most recently saved canvas state by popping the top entry in the drawing state stack. If there is no saved state, this method does nothing.
dom-context-2d-restore-dev.title: CanvasRenderingContext2D: restore() method

dom-context-2d-rotate-dev.name: rotate
dom-context-2d-rotate-dev.summary: The CanvasRenderingContext2D.rotate() method of the Canvas 2D API adds a rotation to the transformation matrix.
dom-context-2d-rotate-dev.title: CanvasRenderingContext2D: rotate() method

dom-context-2d-roundrect.name: roundRect
dom-context-2d-roundrect.summary: The CanvasRenderingContext2D.roundRect() method of the Canvas 2D API adds a rounded rectangle to the current path.
dom-context-2d-roundrect.title: CanvasRenderingContext2D: roundRect() method

dom-context-2d-save-dev.name: save
dom-context-2d-save-dev.summary: The CanvasRenderingContext2D.save() method of the Canvas 2D API saves the entire state of the canvas by pushing the current state onto a stack.
dom-context-2d-save-dev.title: CanvasRenderingContext2D: save() method

dom-context-2d-scale-dev.name: scale
dom-context-2d-scale-dev.summary: The CanvasRenderingContext2D.scale() method of the Canvas 2D API adds a scaling transformation to the canvas units horizontally and/or vertically.
dom-context-2d-scale-dev.title: CanvasRenderingContext2D: scale() method

dom-context-2d-scrollpathintoview-dev.name: scrollPathIntoView
dom-context-2d-scrollpathintoview-dev.summary: The CanvasRenderingContext2D.scrollPathIntoView() method of the Canvas 2D API scrolls the current or given path into view. It is similar to Element.scrollIntoView().
dom-context-2d-scrollpathintoview-dev.title: CanvasRenderingContext2D: scrollPathIntoView() method

dom-context-2d-setlinedash-dev.name: setLineDash
dom-context-2d-setlinedash-dev.summary: The setLineDash() method of the Canvas 2D API's CanvasRenderingContext2D interface sets the line dash pattern used when stroking lines. It uses an array of values that specify alternating lengths of lines and gaps which describe the pattern.
dom-context-2d-setlinedash-dev.title: CanvasRenderingContext2D: setLineDash() method

dom-context-2d-settransform-dev.name: setTransform
dom-context-2d-settransform-dev.summary: The CanvasRenderingContext2D.setTransform() method of the Canvas 2D API resets (overrides) the current transformation to the identity matrix, and then invokes a transformation described by the arguments of this method. This lets you scale, rotate, translate (move), and skew the context.
dom-context-2d-settransform-dev.title: CanvasRenderingContext2D: setTransform() method

dom-context-2d-shadowblur-dev.name: shadowBlur
dom-context-2d-shadowblur-dev.summary: The CanvasRenderingContext2D.shadowBlur property of the Canvas 2D API specifies the amount of blur applied to shadows. The default is 0 (no blur).
dom-context-2d-shadowblur-dev.title: CanvasRenderingContext2D: shadowBlur property

dom-context-2d-shadowcolor-dev.name: shadowColor
dom-context-2d-shadowcolor-dev.summary: The CanvasRenderingContext2D.shadowColor property of the Canvas 2D API specifies the color of shadows.
dom-context-2d-shadowcolor-dev.title: CanvasRenderingContext2D: shadowColor property

dom-context-2d-shadowoffsetx-dev.name: shadowOffsetX
dom-context-2d-shadowoffsetx-dev.summary: The CanvasRenderingContext2D.shadowOffsetX property of the Canvas 2D API specifies the distance that shadows will be offset horizontally.
dom-context-2d-shadowoffsetx-dev.title: CanvasRenderingContext2D: shadowOffsetX property

dom-context-2d-shadowoffsety-dev.name: shadowOffsetY
dom-context-2d-shadowoffsety-dev.summary: The CanvasRenderingContext2D.shadowOffsetY property of the Canvas 2D API specifies the distance that shadows will be offset vertically.
dom-context-2d-shadowoffsety-dev.title: CanvasRenderingContext2D: shadowOffsetY property

dom-context-2d-stroke-dev.name: stroke
dom-context-2d-stroke-dev.summary: The CanvasRenderingContext2D.stroke() method of the Canvas 2D API strokes (outlines) the current or given path with the current stroke style.
dom-context-2d-stroke-dev.title: CanvasRenderingContext2D: stroke() method

dom-context-2d-strokerect-dev.name: strokeRect
dom-context-2d-strokerect-dev.summary: The CanvasRenderingContext2D.strokeRect() method of the Canvas 2D API draws a rectangle that is stroked (outlined) according to the current strokeStyle and other context settings.
dom-context-2d-strokerect-dev.title: CanvasRenderingContext2D: strokeRect() method

dom-context-2d-strokestyle-dev.name: strokeStyle
dom-context-2d-strokestyle-dev.summary: The CanvasRenderingContext2D.strokeStyle property of the Canvas 2D API specifies the color, gradient, or pattern to use for the strokes (outlines) around shapes. The default is #000 (black).
dom-context-2d-strokestyle-dev.title: CanvasRenderingContext2D: strokeStyle property

dom-context-2d-stroketext-dev.name: strokeText
dom-context-2d-stroketext-dev.summary: The CanvasRenderingContext2D method strokeText(), part of the Canvas 2D API, strokes  that is, draws the outlines of  the characters of a text string at the specified coordinates. An optional parameter allows specifying a maximum width for the rendered text, which the user agent will achieve by condensing the text or by using a lower font size.
dom-context-2d-stroketext-dev.title: CanvasRenderingContext2D: strokeText() method

dom-context-2d-textalign-dev.name: textAlign
dom-context-2d-textalign-dev.summary: The CanvasRenderingContext2D.textAlign property of the Canvas 2D API specifies the current text alignment used when drawing text.
dom-context-2d-textalign-dev.title: CanvasRenderingContext2D: textAlign property

dom-context-2d-textbaseline-dev.name: textBaseline
dom-context-2d-textbaseline-dev.summary: The CanvasRenderingContext2D.textBaseline property of the Canvas 2D API specifies the current text baseline used when drawing text.
dom-context-2d-textbaseline-dev.title: CanvasRenderingContext2D: textBaseline property

dom-context-2d-textrendering.name: textRendering
dom-context-2d-textrendering.summary: The CanvasRenderingContext2D.textRendering property of the Canvas API provides information to the rendering engine about what to optimize for when rendering text.
dom-context-2d-textrendering.title: CanvasRenderingContext2D: textRendering property

dom-context-2d-transform-dev.name: transform
dom-context-2d-transform-dev.summary: The CanvasRenderingContext2D.transform() method of the Canvas 2D API multiplies the current transformation with the matrix described by the arguments of this method. This lets you scale, rotate, translate (move), and skew the context.
dom-context-2d-transform-dev.title: CanvasRenderingContext2D: transform() method

dom-context-2d-translate-dev.name: translate
dom-context-2d-translate-dev.summary: The CanvasRenderingContext2D.translate() method of the Canvas 2D API adds a translation transformation to the current matrix.
dom-context-2d-translate-dev.title: CanvasRenderingContext2D: translate() method

dom-context-2d-wordspacing.name: wordSpacing
dom-context-2d-wordspacing.summary: The CanvasRenderingContext2D.wordSpacing property of the Canvas API specifies the spacing between words when drawing text.
dom-context-2d-wordspacing.title: CanvasRenderingContext2D: wordSpacing property

2dcontext.name: CanvasRenderingContext2D
2dcontext.summary: The CanvasRenderingContext2D interface, part of the Canvas API, provides the 2D rendering context for the drawing surface of a <canvas> element. It is used for drawing shapes, text, images, and other objects.
2dcontext.title: CanvasRenderingContext2D

dom-customelementregistry-define-dev.name: define
dom-customelementregistry-define-dev.summary: The define() method of the CustomElementRegistry interface defines a new custom element.
dom-customelementregistry-define-dev.title: CustomElementRegistry: define() method

dom-customelementregistry-get-dev.name: get
dom-customelementregistry-get-dev.summary: The get() method of the CustomElementRegistry interface returns the constructor for a previously-defined custom element.
dom-customelementregistry-get-dev.title: CustomElementRegistry: get() method

dom-customelementregistry-getname.name: getName
dom-customelementregistry-getname.summary: The getName() method of the CustomElementRegistry interface returns the name for a previously-defined custom element.

safari.notes: Supports 'Autonomous custom elements' but not 'Customized built-in elements'.

dom-customelementregistry-getname.title: CustomElementRegistry: getName() method

dom-customelementregistry-upgrade-dev.name: upgrade
dom-customelementregistry-upgrade-dev.summary: The upgrade() method of the CustomElementRegistry interface upgrades all shadow-containing custom elements in a Node subtree, even before they are connected to the main document.
dom-customelementregistry-upgrade-dev.title: CustomElementRegistry: upgrade() method

dom-customelementregistry-whendefined-de.name: whenDefined
dom-customelementregistry-whendefined-de.summary: The whenDefined() method of the CustomElementRegistry interface returns a Promise that resolves when the named element is defined.
dom-customelementregistry-whendefined-de.title: CustomElementRegistry: whenDefined() method

custom-elements-api.name: CustomElementRegistry
custom-elements-api.summary: The CustomElementRegistry interface provides methods for registering custom elements and querying registered elements. To get an instance of it, use the window.customElements property.
custom-elements-api.title: CustomElementRegistry

dom-domparser-constructor-dev.name: DOMParser
dom-domparser-constructor-dev.summary: The DOMParser() constructor creates a new DOMParser object. This object can be used to parse the text of a document using the parseFromString() method.
dom-domparser-constructor-dev.title: DOMParser: DOMParser() constructor

dom-domparser-parsefromstring-dev.name: parseFromString
dom-domparser-parsefromstring-dev.summary: The parseFromString() method of the DOMParser interface parses a string containing either HTML or XML, returning an HTMLDocument or an XMLDocument.
dom-domparser-parsefromstring-dev.title: DOMParser: parseFromString() method

dom-parsing-and-serialization.name: DOMParser
dom-parsing-and-serialization.summary: The DOMParser interface provides the ability to parse XML or HTML source code from a string into a DOM Document.
dom-parsing-and-serialization.title: DOMParser

dom-domstringlist-contains.name: contains
dom-domstringlist-contains.summary: The contains() method returns a boolean indicating whether the given string is in the list.
dom-domstringlist-contains.title: DOMStringList: contains() method

dom-domstringlist-item.name: item
dom-domstringlist-item.summary: The item() method returns a string from a DOMStringList by index.
dom-domstringlist-item.title: DOMStringList: item() method

dom-domstringlist-length.name: length
dom-domstringlist-length.summary: The read-only length property indicates the number of strings in the DOMStringList.
dom-domstringlist-length.title: DOMStringList: length property

the-domstringlist-interface.name: DOMStringList
the-domstringlist-interface.summary: The DOMString interface is a legacy type returned by some APIs and represents a non-modifiable list of strings (DOMString). Modern APIs use Array objects (in WebIDL: sequence<DOMString>) instead.
the-domstringlist-interface.title: DOMStringList

embedding-custom-non-visible-data-with-t.name: DOMStringMap
embedding-custom-non-visible-data-with-t.summary: The DOMStringMap interface is used for the HTMLElement.dataset/SVGElement.dataset attribute, to represent data for custom attributes added to elements.
embedding-custom-non-visible-data-with-t.title: DOMStringMap

dom-datatransfer-dev.name: DataTransfer
dom-datatransfer-dev.summary: The DataTransfer constructor creates a new DataTransfer object instance.
dom-datatransfer-dev.title: DataTransfer: DataTransfer() constructor

dom-datatransfer-cleardata-dev.name: clearData
dom-datatransfer-cleardata-dev.summary: The DataTransfer.clearData() method removes the drag operation's drag data for the given type. If data for the given type does not exist, this method does nothing.
dom-datatransfer-cleardata-dev.title: DataTransfer: clearData() method

dom-datatransfer-dropeffect-dev.name: dropEffect
dom-datatransfer-dropeffect-dev.summary: The DataTransfer.dropEffect property controls the feedback (typically visual) the user is given during a drag and drop operation. It will affect which cursor is displayed while dragging. For example, when the user hovers over a target drop element, the browser's cursor may indicate which type of operation will occur.
dom-datatransfer-dropeffect-dev.title: DataTransfer: dropEffect property

dom-datatransfer-effectallowed-dev.name: effectAllowed
dom-datatransfer-effectallowed-dev.summary: The DataTransfer.effectAllowed property specifies the effect that is allowed for a drag operation. The copy operation is used to indicate that the data being dragged will be copied from its present location to the drop location. The move operation is used to indicate that the data being dragged will be moved, and the link operation is used to indicate that some form of relationship or connection will be created between the source and drop locations.
dom-datatransfer-effectallowed-dev.title: DataTransfer: effectAllowed property

dom-datatransfer-files-dev.name: files
dom-datatransfer-files-dev.summary: The files property of DataTransfer objects is a list of the files in the drag operation. If the operation includes no files, the list is empty.
dom-datatransfer-files-dev.title: DataTransfer: files property

dom-datatransfer-getdata-dev.name: getData
dom-datatransfer-getdata-dev.summary: The DataTransfer.getData() method retrieves drag data (as a string) for the specified type. If the drag operation does not include data, this method returns an empty string.
dom-datatransfer-getdata-dev.title: DataTransfer: getData() method

dom-datatransfer-items-dev.name: items
dom-datatransfer-items-dev.summary: The read-only DataTransfer property items property is a list of the data transfer items in a drag operation. The list includes one item for each item in the operation and if the operation had no items, the list is empty.
dom-datatransfer-items-dev.title: DataTransfer: items property

dom-datatransfer-setdata-dev.name: setData
dom-datatransfer-setdata-dev.summary: The DataTransfer.setData() method sets the drag operation's drag data to the specified data and type. If data for the given type does not exist, it is added at the end of the drag data store, such that the last item in the types list will be the new type. If data for the given type already exists, the existing data is replaced in the same position. That is, the order of the types list is not changed when replacing data of the same type.
dom-datatransfer-setdata-dev.title: DataTransfer: setData() method

dom-datatransfer-setdragimage-dev.name: setDragImage
dom-datatransfer-setdragimage-dev.summary: When a drag occurs, a translucent image is generated from the drag target (the element the dragstart event is fired at), and follows the mouse pointer during the drag. This image is created automatically, so you do not need to create it yourself. However, if a custom image is desired, the DataTransfer.setDragImage() method can be used to set the custom image to be used. The image will typically be an element but it can also be a or any other visible element.
dom-datatransfer-setdragimage-dev.title: DataTransfer: setDragImage() method

dom-datatransfer-types-dev.name: types
dom-datatransfer-types-dev.summary: The DataTransfer.types read-only property returns the available types that exist in the items.

notes: The property returns a DOMStringList.
Text is returned instead of text/plain

opera.notes: As of Opera 12, Text is returned instead of text/plain

dom-datatransfer-types-dev.title: DataTransfer: types property

the-datatransfer-interface.name: DataTransfer
the-datatransfer-interface.summary: The DataTransfer object is used to hold the data that is being dragged during a drag and drop operation. It may hold one or more data items, each of one or more data types. For more information about drag and drop, see HTML Drag and Drop API.

firefox.notes: As of Firefox 52, the DataTransfer.types property returns a frozen array of DOMStrings as per spec, rather than a DOMStringList.

the-datatransfer-interface.title: DataTransfer

dom-datatransferitem-getasfile-dev.name: getAsFile
dom-datatransferitem-getasfile-dev.summary: If the item is a file, the DataTransferItem.getAsFile() method returns the drag data item's File object. If the item is not a file, this method returns null.
dom-datatransferitem-getasfile-dev.title: DataTransferItem: getAsFile() method

dom-datatransferitem-getasstring-dev.name: getAsString
dom-datatransferitem-getasstring-dev.summary: The DataTransferItem.getAsString() method invokes the given callback with the drag data item's string data as the argument if the item's kind is a Plain unicode string (i.e. kind is string).
dom-datatransferitem-getasstring-dev.title: DataTransferItem: getAsString() method

dom-datatransferitem-kind-dev.name: kind
dom-datatransferitem-kind-dev.summary: The read-only DataTransferItem.kind property returns a DataTransferItem representing the drag data item kind: some text or some file.
dom-datatransferitem-kind-dev.title: DataTransferItem: kind property

dom-datatransferitem-type-dev.name: type
dom-datatransferitem-type-dev.summary: The read-only DataTransferItem.type property returns the type (format) of the DataTransferItem object representing the drag data item. The type is a Unicode string generally given by a MIME type, although a MIME type is not required.
dom-datatransferitem-type-dev.title: DataTransferItem: type property

the-datatransferitem-interface.name: DataTransferItem
the-datatransferitem-interface.summary: The DataTransferItem object represents one drag data item. During a drag operation, each drag event has a dataTransfer property which contains a list of drag data items. Each item in the list is a DataTransferItem object.
the-datatransferitem-interface.title: DataTransferItem

dom-datatransferitemlist-add-dev.name: add
dom-datatransferitemlist-add-dev.summary: The DataTransferItemList.add() method creates a new DataTransferItem using the specified data and adds it to the drag data list. The item may be a File or a string of a given type. If the item is successfully added to the list, the newly-created DataTransferItem object is returned.
dom-datatransferitemlist-add-dev.title: DataTransferItemList: add() method

dom-datatransferitemlist-clear-dev.name: clear
dom-datatransferitemlist-clear-dev.summary: The DataTransferItemList method clear() removes all DataTransferItem objects from the drag data items list, leaving the list empty.
dom-datatransferitemlist-clear-dev.title: DataTransferItemList: clear() method

dom-datatransferitemlist-length-dev.name: length
dom-datatransferitemlist-length-dev.summary: The read-only length property of the DataTransferItemList interface returns the number of items currently in the drag item list.
dom-datatransferitemlist-length-dev.title: DataTransferItemList: length property

dom-datatransferitemlist-remove-dev.name: remove
dom-datatransferitemlist-remove-dev.summary: The DataTransferItemList.remove() method removes the DataTransferItem at the specified index from the list. If the index is less than zero or greater than one less than the length of the list, the list will not be changed.
dom-datatransferitemlist-remove-dev.title: DataTransferItemList: remove() method

the-datatransferitemlist-interface.name: DataTransferItemList
the-datatransferitemlist-interface.summary: The DataTransferItemList object is a list of DataTransferItem objects representing items being dragged. During a drag operation, each DragEvent has a dataTransfer property and that property is a DataTransferItemList.
the-datatransferitemlist-interface.title: DataTransferItemList

dom-dedicatedworkerglobalscope-close-dev.name: close
dom-dedicatedworkerglobalscope-close-dev.summary: The close() method of the DedicatedWorkerGlobalScope interface discards any tasks queued in the DedicatedWorkerGlobalScope's event loop, effectively closing this particular scope.
dom-dedicatedworkerglobalscope-close-dev.title: DedicatedWorkerGlobalScope: close() method

handler-dedicatedworkerglobalscope-onmes.name: message_event
handler-dedicatedworkerglobalscope-onmes.summary: The message event is fired on a DedicatedWorkerGlobalScope object when the worker receives a message from its parent (i.e. when the parent sends a message using Worker.postMessage()).
handler-dedicatedworkerglobalscope-onmes.title: DedicatedWorkerGlobalScope: message event

handler-dedicatedworkerglobalscope-onmes.name: messageerror_event
handler-dedicatedworkerglobalscope-onmes.summary: The messageerror event is fired on a DedicatedWorkerGlobalScope object when it receives a message that can't be deserialized.

safari.notes: See bug 171216.

handler-dedicatedworkerglobalscope-onmes.title: DedicatedWorkerGlobalScope: messageerror event

dom-dedicatedworkerglobalscope-name-dev.name: name
dom-dedicatedworkerglobalscope-name-dev.summary: The name read-only property of the DedicatedWorkerGlobalScope interface returns the name that the Worker was (optionally) given when it was created. This is the name that the Worker() constructor can pass to get a reference to the DedicatedWorkerGlobalScope.
dom-dedicatedworkerglobalscope-name-dev.title: DedicatedWorkerGlobalScope: name property

dom-dedicatedworkerglobalscope-postmessa.name: postMessage
dom-dedicatedworkerglobalscope-postmessa.summary: The postMessage() method of the DedicatedWorkerGlobalScope interface sends a message to the main thread that spawned it.

deno.notes: The message parameter does not support cloning Blob values.

notes: The message parameter does not support cloning Blob values.
The transfer parameter does not accept ArrayBuffer items. Passing an ArrayBuffer results in an error being thrown.
The message parameter does not support cloning SharedArrayBuffer or Blob values.
The transfer parameter is ignored.
Data passed in the message parameter is serialized with JSON, not the structured clone algorithm.
The transfer parameter is ignored.

dom-dedicatedworkerglobalscope-postmessa.title: DedicatedWorkerGlobalScope: postMessage() method

dedicated-workers-and-the-dedicatedworke.name: DedicatedWorkerGlobalScope
dedicated-workers-and-the-dedicatedworke.summary: The DedicatedWorkerGlobalScope object (the Worker global scope) is accessible through the self keyword. Some additional global functions, namespaces objects, and constructors, not typically associated with the worker global scope, but available on it, are listed in the JavaScript Reference. See also: Functions available to workers.
dedicated-workers-and-the-dedicatedworke.title: DedicatedWorkerGlobalScope

stop-parsing.name: DOMContentLoaded_event
stop-parsing.summary: The DOMContentLoaded event fires when the initial HTML document has been completely loaded and parsed, without waiting for stylesheets, images, and subframes to finish loading.
stop-parsing.title: Document: DOMContentLoaded event

dom-documentorshadowroot-activeelement-d.name: activeElement
dom-documentorshadowroot-activeelement-d.summary: The activeElement read-only property of the Document interface returns the Element within the DOM that currently has focus.
dom-documentorshadowroot-activeelement-d.title: Document: activeElement property

dom-documentorshadowroot-activeelement-d.name: activeElement
dom-documentorshadowroot-activeelement-d.summary: The activeElement read-only property of the ShadowRoot interface returns the element within the shadow tree that has focus.
dom-documentorshadowroot-activeelement-d.title: ShadowRoot: activeElement property

dom-document-body-dev.name: body
dom-document-body-dev.summary: The Document.body property represents the <body> or <frameset> node of the current document, or null if no such element exists.

firefox.notes: Only supported for HTMLDocument, not all Document objects.

dom-document-body-dev.title: Document: body property

dom-document-close-dev.name: close
dom-document-close-dev.summary: The Document.close() method finishes writing to a document, opened with Document.open().

chrome.notes: Only supported for HTMLDocument, not all Document objects.

opera.notes: Only supported for HTMLDocument, not all Document objects.

opera_android.notes: Only supported for HTMLDocument, not all Document objects.

safari.notes: Only supported for HTMLDocument, not all Document objects.

edge_blink.notes: Only supported for HTMLDocument, not all Document objects.

dom-document-close-dev.title: Document: close() method

dom-document-cookie.name: cookie
dom-document-cookie.summary: The Document property cookie lets you read and write cookies associated with the document. It serves as a getter and setter for the actual values of the cookies.

firefox.notes: Before Firefox 68, cookie was available only on HTML documents; it is now available on all documents, such as XML and SVG.

dom-document-cookie.title: Document: cookie property

dom-document-currentscript-dev.name: currentScript
dom-document-currentscript-dev.summary: The Document.currentScript property returns the <script> element whose script is currently being processed and isn't a JavaScript module. (For modules use import.meta instead.)
dom-document-currentscript-dev.title: Document: currentScript property

dom-document-defaultview-dev.name: defaultView
dom-document-defaultview-dev.summary: In browsers, document.defaultView returns the window object associated with a document, or null if none is available.
dom-document-defaultview-dev.title: Document: defaultView property

dom-document-designmode-dev.name: designMode
dom-document-designmode-dev.summary: document.designMode controls whether the entire document is editable. Valid values are "on" and "off". According to the specification, this property is meant to default to "off". Firefox follows this standard. The earlier versions of Chrome and IE default to "inherit". Starting in Chrome 43, the default is "off" and "inherit" is no longer supported. In IE6-10, the value is capitalized.
dom-document-designmode-dev.title: Document: designMode property

dom-document-dir.name: dir
dom-document-dir.summary: The Document.dir property is a string representing the directionality of the text of the document, whether left to right (default) or right to left. Possible values are 'rtl', right to left, and 'ltr', left to right.

chrome.notes: Only supported for HTMLDocument, not all Document objects.

firefox.notes: Incorrect behavior before Firefox 23.

opera.notes: Only supported for HTMLDocument, not all Document objects.

opera_android.notes: Only supported for HTMLDocument, not all Document objects.

safari.notes: Only supported for HTMLDocument, not all Document objects.

edge_blink.notes: Only supported for HTMLDocument, not all Document objects.

dom-document-dir.title: Document: dir property

dom-document-embeds-dev.name: embeds
dom-document-embeds-dev.summary: The embeds read-only property of the Document interface returns a list of the embedded <embed> elements within the current document.

chrome.notes: Only supported for HTMLDocument, not all Document objects.

opera.notes: Only supported for HTMLDocument, not all Document objects.

opera_android.notes: Only supported for HTMLDocument, not all Document objects.

safari.notes: Only supported for HTMLDocument, not all Document objects.

edge_blink.notes: Only supported for HTMLDocument, not all Document objects.

dom-document-embeds-dev.title: Document: embeds property

dom-document-forms-dev.name: forms
dom-document-forms-dev.summary: The forms read-only property of the Document interface returns an HTMLCollection listing all the <form> elements contained in the document.
dom-document-forms-dev.title: Document: forms property

dom-document-getelementsbyname-dev.name: getElementsByName
dom-document-getelementsbyname-dev.summary: The getElementsByName() method of the Document object returns a NodeList Collection of elements with a given name attribute in the document.

ie.notes: Returns an HTMLCollection, not a NodeList

dom-document-getelementsbyname-dev.title: Document: getElementsByName() method

dom-document-hasfocus-dev.name: hasFocus
dom-document-hasfocus-dev.summary: The hasFocus() method of the Document interface returns a boolean value indicating whether the document or any element inside the document has focus. This method can be used to determine whether the active element in a document has focus.
dom-document-hasfocus-dev.title: Document: hasFocus() method

dom-document-head-dev.name: head
dom-document-head-dev.summary: The head read-only property of the Document interface returns the <head> element of the current document.
dom-document-head-dev.title: Document: head property

dom-document-hidden.name: hidden
dom-document-hidden.summary: The Document.hidden read-only property returns a Boolean value indicating if the page is considered hidden or not.

firefox.notes: Since Firefox 56 it also returns true on macOS when the window is completely hidden by another non-translucent application.

dom-document-hidden.title: Document: hidden property

dom-document-images-dev.name: images
dom-document-images-dev.summary: The images read-only property of the Document interface returns a collection of the images in the current HTML document.
dom-document-images-dev.title: Document: images property

dom-document-lastmodified-dev.name: lastModified
dom-document-lastmodified-dev.summary: The lastModified property of the Document interface returns a string containing the date and time on which the current document was last modified.
dom-document-lastmodified-dev.title: Document: lastModified property

dom-document-links-dev.name: links
dom-document-links-dev.summary: The links read-only property of the Document interface returns a collection of all <area> elements and <a> elements in a document with a value for the href attribute.
dom-document-links-dev.title: Document: links property

the-location-interface.name: location
the-location-interface.summary: The Document.location read-only property returns a Location object, which contains information about the URL of the document and provides methods for changing that URL and loading another URL.
the-location-interface.title: Document: location property

the-location-interface.name: Location
the-location-interface.summary: The Location interface represents the location (URL) of the object it is linked to. Changes done on it are reflected on the object it relates to. Both the Document and Window interface have such a linked Location, accessible via Document.location and Window.location respectively.
the-location-interface.title: Location

the-location-interface.name: location
the-location-interface.summary: The Window.location read-only property returns a Location object with information about the current location of the document.

firefox.notes: Before Firefox 57, single quotes contained in URLs were escaped when accessed via URL APIs. See bug 1386683.

the-location-interface.title: Window: location property

dom-document-open-dev.name: open
dom-document-open-dev.summary: The Document.open() method opens a document for writing.

chrome.notes: Only supported for HTMLDocument, not all Document objects.

opera.notes: Only supported for HTMLDocument, not all Document objects.

opera_android.notes: Only supported for HTMLDocument, not all Document objects.

safari.notes: Only supported for HTMLDocument, not all Document objects.

edge_blink.notes: Only supported for HTMLDocument, not all Document objects.

dom-document-open-dev.title: Document: open() method

dom-document-plugins-dev.name: plugins
dom-document-plugins-dev.summary: The plugins read-only property of the Document interface returns an HTMLCollection object containing one or more HTMLEmbedElements representing the <embed> elements in the current document.

chrome.notes: Only supported for HTMLDocument, not all Document objects.

opera.notes: Only supported for HTMLDocument, not all Document objects.

opera_android.notes: Only supported for HTMLDocument, not all Document objects.

safari.notes: Only supported for HTMLDocument, not all Document objects.

safari_ios.notes: Only supported for HTMLDocument, not all Document objects.

edge_blink.notes: Only supported for HTMLDocument, not all Document objects.

dom-document-plugins-dev.title: Document: plugins property

current-document-readiness.name: readyState
current-document-readiness.summary: The Document.readyState property describes the loading state of the document. When the value of this property changes, a readystatechange event fires on the document object.

ie.notes: Internet Explorer 9 and 10 have bugs where the 'interactive' state can be fired too early before the document has finished parsing.
Only supports 'complete'.

opera.notes: Opera Presto fires 'complete' late after the 'load' event (in an incorrect order as per HTML5 standard specification).

opera_android.notes: Opera Presto fires 'complete' late after the 'load' event (in an incorrect order as per HTML5 standard specification).

current-document-readiness.title: Document: readyState property

event-readystatechange.name: readystatechange_event
event-readystatechange.summary: The readystatechange event is fired when the readyState attribute of a document has changed.
event-readystatechange.title: Document: readystatechange event

dom-document-referrer-dev.name: referrer
dom-document-referrer-dev.summary: The Document.referrer property returns the URI of the page that linked to this page.
dom-document-referrer-dev.title: Document: referrer property

dom-document-scripts-dev.name: scripts
dom-document-scripts-dev.summary: The scripts property of the Document interface returns a list of the <script> elements in the document. The returned object is an HTMLCollection.
dom-document-scripts-dev.title: Document: scripts property

handler-onscroll.name: scroll_event
handler-onscroll.summary: The scroll event fires when the document view has been scrolled. To detect when scrolling has completed, see the Document: scrollend event. For element scrolling, see Element: scroll event.
handler-onscroll.title: Document: scroll event

handler-onscroll.name: scroll_event
handler-onscroll.summary: The scroll event fires when an element has been scrolled. To detect when scrolling has completed, see the Element: scrollend event.
handler-onscroll.title: Element: scroll event

handler-onscrollend.name: scrollend_event
handler-onscrollend.summary: The scrollend event fires when the document view has completed scrolling. Scrolling is considered completed when the scroll position has no more pending updates and the user has completed their gesture.
handler-onscrollend.title: Document: scrollend event

handler-onscrollend.name: scrollend_event
handler-onscrollend.summary: The scrollend event fires when element scrolling has completed. Scrolling is considered completed when the scroll position has no more pending updates and the user has completed their gesture.
handler-onscrollend.title: Element: scrollend event

document.title.name: title
document.title.summary: The document.title property gets or sets the current title of the document. When present, it defaults to the value of the <title>.
document.title.title: Document: title property

event-visibilitychange.name: visibilitychange_event
event-visibilitychange.summary: The visibilitychange event is fired at the document when the contents of its tab have become visible or have been hidden.
