webview_android.notes: Can incorrectly return true, see bug 811122.

dom-navigator-online-dev.title: WorkerNavigator: onLine property

dom-navigator-pdfviewerenabled.name: pdfViewerEnabled
dom-navigator-pdfviewerenabled.summary: The pdfViewerEnabled property of the Navigator interface indicates whether the browser supports inline display of PDF files when navigating to them.
dom-navigator-pdfviewerenabled.title: Navigator: pdfViewerEnabled property

custom-handlers.name: registerProtocolHandler
custom-handlers.summary: The Navigator method registerProtocolHandler() lets websites register their ability to open or handle particular URL schemes (aka protocols).

chrome.notes: From Chrome 77, the URL parameter only accepts http or https URLs.

edge_blink.notes: From Chrome 77, the URL parameter only accepts http or https URLs.

custom-handlers.title: Navigator: registerProtocolHandler() method

dom-navigator-unregisterprotocolhandler-.name: unregisterProtocolHandler
dom-navigator-unregisterprotocolhandler-.summary: The Navigator method unregisterProtocolHandler() removes a protocol handler for a given URL scheme.
dom-navigator-unregisterprotocolhandler-.title: Navigator: unregisterProtocolHandler() method

dom-navigator-useractivation.name: userActivation
dom-navigator-useractivation.summary: The read-only userActivation property of the Navigator interface returns a UserActivation object which contains information about the current window's user activation state.
dom-navigator-useractivation.title: Navigator: userActivation property

dom-navigator-useragent-dev.name: userAgent
dom-navigator-useragent-dev.summary: The Navigator.userAgent read-only property returns the user agent string for the current browser.
dom-navigator-useragent-dev.title: Navigator: userAgent property

dom-navigator-useragent-dev.name: userAgent
dom-navigator-useragent-dev.summary: The WorkerNavigator.userAgent read-only property returns the user agent string for the current browser.
dom-navigator-useragent-dev.title: WorkerNavigator: userAgent property

the-navigator-object.name: Navigator
the-navigator-object.summary: The Navigator interface represents the state and the identity of the user agent. It allows scripts to query it and to register themselves to carry on some activities.
the-navigator-object.title: Navigator

dom-offscreencanvas-dev.name: OffscreenCanvas
dom-offscreencanvas-dev.summary: The OffscreenCanvas() constructor returns a newly instantiated OffscreenCanvas object.
dom-offscreencanvas-dev.title: OffscreenCanvas: OffscreenCanvas() constructor

dom-offscreencanvas-converttoblob-dev.name: convertToBlob
dom-offscreencanvas-converttoblob-dev.summary: The OffscreenCanvas.convertToBlob() method creates a Blob object representing the image contained in the canvas.
dom-offscreencanvas-converttoblob-dev.title: OffscreenCanvas: convertToBlob() method

dom-offscreencanvas-getcontext-dev.name: getContext
dom-offscreencanvas-getcontext-dev.summary: The OffscreenCanvas.getContext() method returns a drawing context for an offscreen canvas, or null if the context identifier is not supported.
dom-offscreencanvas-getcontext-dev.title: OffscreenCanvas: getContext() method

dom-offscreencanvas-height-dev.name: height
dom-offscreencanvas-height-dev.summary: The height property returns and sets the height of an OffscreenCanvas object.
dom-offscreencanvas-height-dev.title: OffscreenCanvas: height property

dom-offscreencanvas-transfertoimagebitma.name: transferToImageBitmap
dom-offscreencanvas-transfertoimagebitma.summary: The OffscreenCanvas.transferToImageBitmap() method creates an ImageBitmap object from the most recently rendered image of the OffscreenCanvas. The OffscreenCanvas allocates a new image for its subsequent rendering.
dom-offscreencanvas-transfertoimagebitma.title: OffscreenCanvas: transferToImageBitmap() method

dom-offscreencanvas-width-dev.name: width
dom-offscreencanvas-width-dev.summary: The width property returns and sets the width of an OffscreenCanvas object.
dom-offscreencanvas-width-dev.title: OffscreenCanvas: width property

the-offscreencanvas-interface.name: OffscreenCanvas
the-offscreencanvas-interface.summary: When using the <canvas> element or the Canvas API, rendering, animation, and user interaction usually happen on the main execution thread of a web application. The computation relating to canvas animations and rendering can have a significant impact on application performance.
the-offscreencanvas-interface.title: OffscreenCanvas

offscreencontext2d-commit.name: commit
offscreencontext2d-commit.summary: The OffscreenCanvasRenderingContext2D.commit() method of the Canvas 2D API copies the rendering context's bitmap to the bitmap of the placeholder <canvas> element of the associated OffscreenCanvas object. The copy operation is synchronous. Calling this method is not needed for the transfer, since it happens automatically during the event-loop execution.
offscreencontext2d-commit.title: OffscreenCanvasRenderingContext2D: commit() method

the-offscreen-2d-rendering-context.name: OffscreenCanvasRenderingContext2D
the-offscreen-2d-rendering-context.summary: The OffscreenCanvasRenderingContext2D interface is a CanvasRenderingContext2D rendering context for drawing to the bitmap of an OffscreenCanvas object. It is similar to the CanvasRenderingContext2D object, with the following differences:
the-offscreen-2d-rendering-context.title: OffscreenCanvasRenderingContext2D

the-pagetransitionevent-interface.name: PageTransitionEvent
the-pagetransitionevent-interface.summary: The PageTransitionEvent() constructor creates a new PageTransitionEvent object, that is used by the pageshow or pagehide events, fired at the window object when a page is loaded or unloaded.
the-pagetransitionevent-interface.title: PageTransitionEvent: PageTransitionEvent() constructor

the-pagetransitionevent-interface.name: PageTransitionEvent
the-pagetransitionevent-interface.summary: The PageTransitionEvent event object is available inside handler functions for the pageshow and pagehide events, fired when a document is being loaded or unloaded.
the-pagetransitionevent-interface.title: PageTransitionEvent

dom-pagetransitionevent-persisted-dev.name: persisted
dom-pagetransitionevent-persisted-dev.summary: The persisted read-only property indicates if a webpage is loading from a cache.

ie.notes: The persisted property is known to be buggy in Internet Explorer. It is advised to check if window.performance.navigation.type == 2 as well.

dom-pagetransitionevent-persisted-dev.title: PageTransitionEvent: persisted property

dom-path2d-dev.name: Path2D
dom-path2d-dev.summary: The Path2D() constructor returns a newly instantiated Path2D object, optionally with another path as an argument (creates a copy), or optionally with a string consisting of SVG path data.
dom-path2d-dev.title: Path2D: Path2D() constructor

dom-path2d-addpath-dev.name: addPath
dom-path2d-addpath-dev.summary: The Path2D.addPath() method of the Canvas 2D API adds one Path2D object to another Path2D object.
dom-path2d-addpath-dev.title: Path2D: addPath() method

path2d-objects.name: Path2D
path2d-objects.summary: The Path2D interface of the Canvas 2D API is used to declare a path that can then be used on a CanvasRenderingContext2D object. The path methods of the CanvasRenderingContext2D interface are also present on this interface, which gives you the convenience of being able to retain and replay your path whenever desired.
path2d-objects.title: Path2D

the-popstateevent-interface.name: PopStateEvent
the-popstateevent-interface.summary: The PopStateEvent() constructor creates a new PopStateEvent object.
the-popstateevent-interface.title: PopStateEvent: PopStateEvent() constructor

the-popstateevent-interface.name: PopStateEvent
the-popstateevent-interface.summary: PopStateEvent is an interface for the popstate event.
the-popstateevent-interface.title: PopStateEvent

dom-popstateevent-state-dev.name: state
dom-popstateevent-state-dev.summary: The state read-only property of the PopStateEvent interface represents the state stored when the event was created.
dom-popstateevent-state-dev.title: PopStateEvent: state property

unhandled-promise-rejections:dom-event-c.name: PromiseRejectionEvent
unhandled-promise-rejections:dom-event-c.summary: The PromiseRejectionEvent() constructor returns a new PromiseRejectionEvent object, which represents events fired when a JavaScript Promise is rejected.
unhandled-promise-rejections:dom-event-c.title: PromiseRejectionEvent: PromiseRejectionEvent() constructor

dom-promiserejectionevent-promise.name: promise
dom-promiserejectionevent-promise.summary: The PromiseRejectionEvent interface's promise read-only property indicates the JavaScript Promise which was rejected. You can examine the event's PromiseRejectionEvent.reason property to learn why the promise was rejected.
dom-promiserejectionevent-promise.title: PromiseRejectionEvent: promise property

dom-promiserejectionevent-reason.name: reason
dom-promiserejectionevent-reason.summary: The PromiseRejectionEvent reason read-only property is any JavaScript value or Object which provides the reason passed into Promise.reject(). This in theory provides information about why the promise was rejected.
dom-promiserejectionevent-reason.title: PromiseRejectionEvent: reason property

the-promiserejectionevent-interface.name: PromiseRejectionEvent
the-promiserejectionevent-interface.summary: The PromiseRejectionEvent interface represents events which are sent to the global script context when JavaScript Promises are rejected. These events are particularly useful for telemetry and debugging purposes.
the-promiserejectionevent-interface.title: PromiseRejectionEvent

dom-radionodelist-value.name: value
dom-radionodelist-value.summary: If the underlying element collection contains radio buttons, the RadioNodeList.value property represents the checked radio button. On retrieving the value property, the value of the currently checked radio button is returned as a string. If the collection does not contain any radio buttons or none of the radio buttons in the collection is in checked state, the empty string is returned. On setting the value property, the first radio button input element whose value property is equal to the new value will be set to checked.
dom-radionodelist-value.title: RadioNodeList: value property

radionodelist.name: RadioNodeList
radionodelist.summary: The RadioNodeList interface represents a collection of radio elements in a <form> or a <fieldset> element.
radionodelist.title: RadioNodeList

handler-abstractworker-onerror.name: error_event
handler-abstractworker-onerror.summary: The error event fires whenever an error occurs in the service worker.
handler-abstractworker-onerror.title: ServiceWorker: error event

handler-abstractworker-onerror.name: error_event
handler-abstractworker-onerror.summary: The error event of the SharedWorker interface fires when an error occurs in the worker.
handler-abstractworker-onerror.title: SharedWorker: error event

handler-abstractworker-onerror.name: error_event
handler-abstractworker-onerror.summary: The error event of the Worker interface fires when an error occurs in the worker.
handler-abstractworker-onerror.title: Worker: error event

dom-sharedworker-dev.name: SharedWorker
dom-sharedworker-dev.summary: The SharedWorker() constructor creates a SharedWorker object that executes the script at the specified URL. This script must obey the same-origin policy.
dom-sharedworker-dev.title: SharedWorker: SharedWorker() constructor

dom-sharedworker-port-dev.name: port
dom-sharedworker-port-dev.summary: The port property of the SharedWorker interface returns a MessagePort object used to communicate and control the shared worker.
dom-sharedworker-port-dev.title: SharedWorker: port property

shared-workers-and-the-sharedworker-inte.name: SharedWorker
shared-workers-and-the-sharedworker-inte.summary: The SharedWorker interface represents a specific kind of worker that can be accessed from several browsing contexts, such as several windows, iframes or even workers. They implement an interface different than dedicated workers and have a different global scope, SharedWorkerGlobalScope.
shared-workers-and-the-sharedworker-inte.title: SharedWorker

dom-sharedworkerglobalscope-close-dev.name: close
dom-sharedworkerglobalscope-close-dev.summary: The close() method of the SharedWorkerGlobalScope interface discards any tasks queued in the SharedWorkerGlobalScope's event loop, effectively closing this particular scope.
dom-sharedworkerglobalscope-close-dev.title: SharedWorkerGlobalScope: close() method

event-workerglobalscope-connect.name: connect_event
event-workerglobalscope-connect.summary: The connect event is fired in shared workers at their SharedWorkerGlobalScope when a new client connects.

firefox.notes: Before version 65 the data property of the event object was null; it is now initialized to an empty string, as per spec.

event-workerglobalscope-connect.title: SharedWorkerGlobalScope: connect event

handler-sharedworkerglobalscope-onconnec.name: connect_event
handler-sharedworkerglobalscope-onconnec.summary: The connect event is fired in shared workers at their SharedWorkerGlobalScope when a new client connects.

firefox.notes: Before version 65 the data property of the event object was null; it is now initialized to an empty string, as per spec.

handler-sharedworkerglobalscope-onconnec.title: SharedWorkerGlobalScope: connect event

dom-sharedworkerglobalscope-name-dev.name: name
dom-sharedworkerglobalscope-name-dev.summary: The name read-only property of the SharedWorkerGlobalScope interface returns the name that the SharedWorker was (optionally) given when it was created. This is the name that the SharedWorker() constructor can pass to get a reference to the SharedWorkerGlobalScope.
dom-sharedworkerglobalscope-name-dev.title: SharedWorkerGlobalScope: name property

shared-workers-and-the-sharedworkergloba.name: SharedWorkerGlobalScope
shared-workers-and-the-sharedworkergloba.summary: The SharedWorkerGlobalScope object (the SharedWorker global scope) is accessible through the self keyword. Some additional global functions, namespaces objects, and constructors, not typically associated with the worker global scope, but available on it, are listed in the JavaScript Reference. See the complete list of functions available to workers.
shared-workers-and-the-sharedworkergloba.title: SharedWorkerGlobalScope

dom-storage-clear-dev.name: clear
dom-storage-clear-dev.summary: The clear() method of the Storage interface clears all keys stored in a given Storage object.
dom-storage-clear-dev.title: Storage: clear() method

dom-storage-getitem-dev.name: getItem
dom-storage-getitem-dev.summary: The getItem() method of the Storage interface, when passed a key name, will return that key's value, or null if the key does not exist, in the given Storage object.
dom-storage-getitem-dev.title: Storage: getItem() method

dom-storage-key-dev.name: key
dom-storage-key-dev.summary: The key() method of the Storage interface, when passed a number n, returns the name of the nth key in a given Storage object. The order of keys is user-agent defined, so you should not rely on it.
dom-storage-key-dev.title: Storage: key() method

dom-storage-length-dev.name: length
dom-storage-length-dev.summary: The length read-only property of the Storage interface returns the number of data items stored in a given Storage object.
dom-storage-length-dev.title: Storage: length property

dom-storage-removeitem-dev.name: removeItem
dom-storage-removeitem-dev.summary: The removeItem() method of the Storage interface, when passed a key name, will remove that key from the given Storage object if it exists. The Storage interface of the Web Storage API provides access to a particular domain's session or local storage.
dom-storage-removeitem-dev.title: Storage: removeItem() method

dom-storage-setitem-dev.name: setItem
dom-storage-setitem-dev.summary: The setItem() method of the Storage interface, when passed a key name and value, will add that key to the given Storage object, or update that key's value if it already exists.
dom-storage-setitem-dev.title: Storage: setItem() method

storage.name: Storage
storage.summary: The Storage interface of the Web Storage API provides access to a particular domain's session or local storage. It allows, for example, the addition, modification, or deletion of stored data items.
storage.title: Storage

the-storageevent-interface.name: StorageEvent
the-storageevent-interface.summary: The StorageEvent interface is implemented by the storage event, which is sent to a window when a storage area the window has access to is changed within the context of another document.
the-storageevent-interface.title: StorageEvent

submitevent.name: SubmitEvent
submitevent.summary: The SubmitEvent() constructor creates and returns a new SubmitEvent object, which is used to represent a submit event fired at an HTML form.
submitevent.title: SubmitEvent: SubmitEvent() constructor

the-submitevent-interface:dom-submiteven.name: submitter
the-submitevent-interface:dom-submiteven.summary: The read-only submitter property found on the SubmitEvent interface specifies the submit button or other element that was invoked to cause the form to be submitted.

safari.notes: Property is not set for <button> elements. See bug 229660.

the-submitevent-interface:dom-submiteven.title: SubmitEvent: submitter property

the-submitevent-interface.name: SubmitEvent
the-submitevent-interface.summary: The SubmitEvent interface defines the object used to represent an HTML form's submit event. This event is fired at the <form> when the form's submit action is invoked.
the-submitevent-interface.title: SubmitEvent

dom-textmetrics-actualboundingboxascent-.name: actualBoundingBoxAscent
dom-textmetrics-actualboundingboxascent-.summary: The read-only actualBoundingBoxAscent property of the TextMetrics interface is a double giving the distance from the horizontal line indicated by the CanvasRenderingContext2D.textBaseline attribute to the top of the bounding rectangle used to render the text, in CSS pixels.
dom-textmetrics-actualboundingboxascent-.title: TextMetrics: actualBoundingBoxAscent property

dom-textmetrics-actualboundingboxdescent.name: actualBoundingBoxDescent
dom-textmetrics-actualboundingboxdescent.summary: The read-only actualBoundingBoxDescent property of the TextMetrics interface is a double giving the distance from the horizontal line indicated by the CanvasRenderingContext2D.textBaseline attribute to the bottom of the bounding rectangle used to render the text, in CSS pixels.
dom-textmetrics-actualboundingboxdescent.title: TextMetrics: actualBoundingBoxDescent property

dom-textmetrics-actualboundingboxleft-de.name: actualBoundingBoxLeft
dom-textmetrics-actualboundingboxleft-de.summary: The read-only actualBoundingBoxLeft property of the TextMetrics interface is a double giving the distance parallel to the baseline from the alignment point given by the CanvasRenderingContext2D.textAlign property to the left side of the bounding rectangle of the given text, in CSS pixels; positive numbers indicating a distance going left from the given alignment point.
dom-textmetrics-actualboundingboxleft-de.title: TextMetrics: actualBoundingBoxLeft property

dom-textmetrics-actualboundingboxright-d.name: actualBoundingBoxRight
dom-textmetrics-actualboundingboxright-d.summary: The read-only actualBoundingBoxRight property of the TextMetrics interface is a double giving the distance parallel to the baseline from the alignment point given by the CanvasRenderingContext2D.textAlign property to the right side of the bounding rectangle of the given text, in CSS pixels.
dom-textmetrics-actualboundingboxright-d.title: TextMetrics: actualBoundingBoxRight property

dom-textmetrics-alphabeticbaseline-dev.name: alphabeticBaseline
dom-textmetrics-alphabeticbaseline-dev.summary: The read-only alphabeticBaseline property of the TextMetrics interface is a double giving the distance from the horizontal line indicated by the CanvasRenderingContext2D.textBaseline property to the alphabetic baseline of the line box, in CSS pixels.
dom-textmetrics-alphabeticbaseline-dev.title: TextMetrics: alphabeticBaseline property

dom-textmetrics-emheightascent-dev.name: emHeightAscent
dom-textmetrics-emheightascent-dev.summary: The read-only emHeightAscent property of the TextMetrics interface is a double giving the distance from the horizontal line indicated by the CanvasRenderingContext2D.textBaseline property to the top of the em square in the line box, in CSS pixels.
dom-textmetrics-emheightascent-dev.title: TextMetrics: emHeightAscent property

dom-textmetrics-emheightdescent-dev.name: emHeightDescent
dom-textmetrics-emheightdescent-dev.summary: The read-only emHeightDescent property of the TextMetrics interface is a double giving the distance from the horizontal line indicated by the CanvasRenderingContext2D.textBaseline property to the bottom of the em square in the line box, in CSS pixels.
dom-textmetrics-emheightdescent-dev.title: TextMetrics: emHeightDescent property

dom-textmetrics-fontboundingboxascent-de.name: fontBoundingBoxAscent
dom-textmetrics-fontboundingboxascent-de.summary: The read-only fontBoundingBoxAscent property of the TextMetrics interface returns the distance from the horizontal line indicated by the CanvasRenderingContext2D.textBaseline attribute, to the top of the highest bounding rectangle of all the fonts used to render the text, in CSS pixels.
dom-textmetrics-fontboundingboxascent-de.title: TextMetrics: fontBoundingBoxAscent property

dom-textmetrics-fontboundingboxdescent-d.name: fontBoundingBoxDescent
dom-textmetrics-fontboundingboxdescent-d.summary: The read-only fontBoundingBoxDescent property of the TextMetrics interface returns the distance from the horizontal line indicated by the CanvasRenderingContext2D.textBaseline attribute to the bottom of the bounding rectangle of all the fonts used to render the text, in CSS pixels.
dom-textmetrics-fontboundingboxdescent-d.title: TextMetrics: fontBoundingBoxDescent property

dom-textmetrics-hangingbaseline-dev.name: hangingBaseline
dom-textmetrics-hangingbaseline-dev.summary: The read-only hangingBaseline property of the TextMetrics interface is a double giving the distance from the horizontal line indicated by the CanvasRenderingContext2D.textBaseline property to the hanging baseline of the line box, in CSS pixels.
dom-textmetrics-hangingbaseline-dev.title: TextMetrics: hangingBaseline property

dom-textmetrics-ideographicbaseline-dev.name: ideographicBaseline
dom-textmetrics-ideographicbaseline-dev.summary: The read-only ideographicBaseline property of the TextMetrics interface is a double giving the distance from the horizontal line indicated by the CanvasRenderingContext2D.textBaseline property to the ideographic baseline of the line box, in CSS pixels.
dom-textmetrics-ideographicbaseline-dev.title: TextMetrics: ideographicBaseline property

dom-textmetrics-width-dev.name: width
dom-textmetrics-width-dev.summary: The read-only width property of the TextMetrics interface contains the text's advance width (the width of that inline box) in CSS pixels.
dom-textmetrics-width-dev.title: TextMetrics: width property

textmetrics.name: TextMetrics
textmetrics.summary: The TextMetrics interface represents the dimensions of a piece of text in the canvas; a TextMetrics instance can be retrieved using the CanvasRenderingContext2D.measureText() method.
textmetrics.title: TextMetrics

dom-texttrack-activecues-dev.name: activeCues
dom-texttrack-activecues-dev.summary: The activeCues read-only property of the TextTrack interface returns a TextTrackCueList object listing the currently active cues.

firefox.notes: Starting in Firefox 69, cues are no longer incorrectly loaded when the TextTrack's mode is disabled; if that's the case, the returned list is empty.

dom-texttrack-activecues-dev.title: TextTrack: activeCues property

dom-texttrack-addcue-dev.name: addCue
dom-texttrack-addcue-dev.summary: The addCue() method of the TextTrack interface adds a new cue to the list of cues.
dom-texttrack-addcue-dev.title: TextTrack: addCue() method

handler-texttrack-oncuechange.name: cuechange_event
handler-texttrack-oncuechange.summary: The cuechange event fires when a TextTrack has changed the currently displaying cues. The event is fired on both the TextTrack and the HTMLTrackElement in which it's being presented, if any.
handler-texttrack-oncuechange.title: TextTrack: cuechange event

dom-texttrack-cues-dev.name: cues
dom-texttrack-cues-dev.summary: The cues read-only property of the TextTrack interface returns a TextTrackCueList object containing all of the track's cues.

firefox.notes: Starting in Firefox 69, cues are no longer incorrectly loaded when the TextTrack's mode is disabled; if that's the case, the returned list is empty.

dom-texttrack-cues-dev.title: TextTrack: cues property

dom-texttrack-id-dev.name: id
dom-texttrack-id-dev.summary: The id read-only property of the TextTrack interface returns the ID of the track if it has one.
dom-texttrack-id-dev.title: TextTrack: id property

dom-texttrack-inbandmetadatatrackdispatc.name: inBandMetadataTrackDispatchType
dom-texttrack-inbandmetadatatrackdispatc.summary: The inBandMetadataTrackDispatchType read-only property of the TextTrack interface returns the text track's in-band metadata dispatch type of the text track represented by the TextTrack object.

chrome.notes: See bug 754093.

edge_blink.notes: See bug 754093.

dom-texttrack-inbandmetadatatrackdispatc.title: TextTrack: inBandMetadataTrackDispatchType property

dom-texttrack-kind-dev.name: kind
dom-texttrack-kind-dev.summary: The kind read-only property of the TextTrack interface returns the kind of text track this object represents. This decides how the track will be handled by a user agent.
dom-texttrack-kind-dev.title: TextTrack: kind property

dom-texttrack-label-dev.name: label
dom-texttrack-label-dev.summary: The label read-only property of the TextTrack interface returns a human-readable label for the text track, if it is available.
dom-texttrack-label-dev.title: TextTrack: label property

dom-texttrack-language-dev.name: language
dom-texttrack-language-dev.summary: The language read-only property of the TextTrack interface returns the language of the text track.
dom-texttrack-language-dev.title: TextTrack: language property

dom-texttrack-mode-dev.name: mode
dom-texttrack-mode-dev.summary: The TextTrack interface's mode property is a string specifying and controlling the text track's mode: disabled, hidden, or showing. You can read this value to determine the current mode, and you can change this value to switch modes.

firefox.notes: Before Firefox 52, using JavaScript to change the mode of a text track that's part of a media element would send one change event to the element's textTracks TextTrackList for each change, even if multiple changes are made in a single pass through the Firefox event loop. Starting in Firefox 52, these changes are reflected by a single event.

dom-texttrack-mode-dev.title: TextTrack: mode property

dom-texttrack-removecue-dev.name: removeCue
dom-texttrack-removecue-dev.summary: The removeCue() method of the TextTrack interface removes a cue from the list of cues.
dom-texttrack-removecue-dev.title: TextTrack: removeCue() method

texttrack.name: TextTrack
texttrack.summary: The TextTrack interfacepart of the API for handling WebVTT (text tracks on media presentations)describes and controls the text track associated with a particular <track> element.

firefox.notes: Firefox versions before Firefox 50 didn't display captions when playing media without one or more video tracks being played.

texttrack.title: TextTrack

dom-texttrackcue-endtime.name: endTime
dom-texttrackcue-endtime.summary: The endTime property of the TextTrackCue interface returns and sets the end time of the cue.
dom-texttrackcue-endtime.title: TextTrackCue: endTime property

event-media-enter.name: enter_event
event-media-enter.summary: The enter event fires when a cue becomes active. In the case of subtitles or a caption this is when it displays over the media.
event-media-enter.title: TextTrackCue: enter event

handler-texttrackcue-onenter.name: enter_event
handler-texttrackcue-onenter.summary: The enter event fires when a cue becomes active. In the case of subtitles or a caption this is when it displays over the media.
handler-texttrackcue-onenter.title: TextTrackCue: enter event

event-media-exit.name: exit_event
event-media-exit.summary: The exit event fires when a cue stops being active.
event-media-exit.title: TextTrackCue: exit event

handler-texttrackcue-onexit.name: exit_event
handler-texttrackcue-onexit.summary: The exit event fires when a cue stops being active.
handler-texttrackcue-onexit.title: TextTrackCue: exit event

dom-texttrackcue-id.name: id
dom-texttrackcue-id.summary: The id property of the TextTrackCue interface returns and sets the identifier for this cue.
dom-texttrackcue-id.title: TextTrackCue: id property

dom-texttrackcue-pauseonexit.name: pauseOnExit
dom-texttrackcue-pauseonexit.summary: The pauseOnExit property of the TextTrackCue interface returns or sets the flag indicating whether playback of the media should pause when the end of the range to which this cue applies is reached.
dom-texttrackcue-pauseonexit.title: TextTrackCue: pauseOnExit property

dom-texttrackcue-starttime.name: startTime
dom-texttrackcue-starttime.summary: The startTime property of the TextTrackCue interface returns and sets the start time of the cue.
dom-texttrackcue-starttime.title: TextTrackCue: startTime property

dom-texttrackcue-track.name: track
dom-texttrackcue-track.summary: The track read-only property of the TextTrackCue interface returns the TextTrack object that this cue belongs to.
dom-texttrackcue-track.title: TextTrackCue: track property

texttrackcue.name: TextTrackCue
texttrackcue.summary: TextTrackCue is an abstract class which is used as the basis for the various derived cue types, such as VTTCue; you will instead work with those derived types. These cues represent strings of text presented for some duration of time during the performance of a TextTrack. The cue includes the start time (the time at which the text will be displayed) and the end time (the time at which it will be removed from the display), as well as other information.
texttrackcue.title: TextTrackCue

dom-texttrackcuelist-getcuebyid.name: getCueById
dom-texttrackcuelist-getcuebyid.summary: The getCueById() method of the TextTrackCueList interface returns the first VTTCue in the list represented by the TextTrackCueList object whose identifier matches the value of id.
dom-texttrackcuelist-getcuebyid.title: TextTrackCueList: getCueById() method

dom-texttrackcuelist-length.name: length
dom-texttrackcuelist-length.summary: The length read-only property of the TextTrackCueList interface returns the number of cues in the list.
dom-texttrackcuelist-length.title: TextTrackCueList: length property

texttrackcuelist.name: TextTrackCueList
texttrackcuelist.summary: The TextTrackCueList array-like object represents a dynamically updating list of TextTrackCue objects.
texttrackcuelist.title: TextTrackCueList

dom-texttracklist-gettrackbyid-dev.name: getTrackById
dom-texttracklist-gettrackbyid-dev.summary: The TextTrackList method getTrackById() returns the first TextTrack object from the track list whose id matches the specified string. This lets you find a specified track if you know its ID string.
dom-texttracklist-gettrackbyid-dev.title: TextTrackList: getTrackById() method

dom-texttracklist-length.name: length
dom-texttracklist-length.summary: The read-only TextTrackList property length returns the number of entries in the TextTrackList, each of which is a TextTrack representing one track in the media element.
dom-texttracklist-length.title: TextTrackList: length property

text-track-api.name: TextTrackList
text-track-api.summary: The TextTrackList interface is used to represent a list of the text tracks defined by the <track> element, with each track represented by a separate textTrack object in the list.
text-track-api.title: TextTrackList

dom-timeranges-end-dev.name: end
dom-timeranges-end-dev.summary: The end() method of the TimeRanges interface returns the time offset at which a specified time range ends.
dom-timeranges-end-dev.title: TimeRanges: end() method

dom-timeranges-length-dev.name: length
dom-timeranges-length-dev.summary: The TimeRanges.length read-only property returns the number of ranges in the object.
dom-timeranges-length-dev.title: TimeRanges: length property

dom-timeranges-start-dev.name: start
dom-timeranges-start-dev.summary: The start() method of the TimeRanges interface returns the time offset at which a specified time range begins.
dom-timeranges-start-dev.title: TimeRanges: start() method

time-ranges.name: TimeRanges
time-ranges.summary: When loading a media resource for use by an <audio> or <video> element, the TimeRanges interface is used for representing the time ranges of the media resource that have been buffered, the time ranges that have been played, and the time ranges that are seekable.
time-ranges.title: TimeRanges

toggleevent.name: ToggleEvent
toggleevent.summary: The ToggleEvent() constructor creates a new ToggleEvent object.
toggleevent.title: ToggleEvent: ToggleEvent() constructor

toggleevent.name: ToggleEvent
toggleevent.summary: The ToggleEvent interface represents an event notifying the user when a popover element's state toggles between showing and hidden.
toggleevent.title: ToggleEvent

dom-toggleevent-newstate.name: newState
dom-toggleevent-newstate.summary: The newState read-only property of the ToggleEvent interface is a string representing the state the element is transitioning to.
dom-toggleevent-newstate.title: ToggleEvent: newState property

dom-toggleevent-oldstate.name: oldState
dom-toggleevent-oldstate.summary: The oldState read-only property of the ToggleEvent interface is a string representing the state the element is transitioning from.
dom-toggleevent-oldstate.title: ToggleEvent: oldState property

dom-trackevent-track-dev.name: track
dom-trackevent-track-dev.summary: The read-only track property of the TrackEvent interface specifies the media track object to which the event applies.
dom-trackevent-track-dev.title: TrackEvent: track property

the-trackevent-interface.name: TrackEvent
the-trackevent-interface.summary: The TrackEvent interface, which is part of the HTML DOM specification, is used for events which represent changes to a set of available tracks on an HTML media element; these events are addtrack and removetrack.
the-trackevent-interface.title: TrackEvent

dom-useractivation-hasbeenactive.name: hasBeenActive
dom-useractivation-hasbeenactive.summary: The read-only hasBeenActive property of the UserActivation interface indicates whether the current window has sticky user activation (see sticky activation).
dom-useractivation-hasbeenactive.title: UserActivation: hasBeenActive property

dom-useractivation-isactive.name: isActive
dom-useractivation-isactive.summary: The read-only hasBeenActive property of the UserActivation interface indicates whether the current window has sticky user activation (see sticky activation).
dom-useractivation-isactive.title: UserActivation: hasBeenActive property

the-useractivation-interface.name: UserActivation
the-useractivation-interface.summary: The UserActivation interface allows querying information about a window's user activation state.
the-useractivation-interface.title: UserActivation

dom-validitystate-badinput-dev.name: badInput
dom-validitystate-badinput-dev.summary: The read-only badInput property of a ValidityState object indicates if the user has provided input that the browser is unable to convert. For example, if you have a number input element whose content is a string.
dom-validitystate-badinput-dev.title: ValidityState: badInput property

dom-validitystate-patternmismatch.name: patternMismatch
dom-validitystate-patternmismatch.summary: The read-only patternMismatch property of a ValidityState object indicates if the value of an <input>, after having been edited by the user, does not conform to the constraints set by the element's pattern attribute.
dom-validitystate-patternmismatch.title: ValidityState: patternMismatch property

dom-validitystate-rangeoverflow.name: rangeOverflow
dom-validitystate-rangeoverflow.summary: The read-only rangeOverflow property of a ValidityState object indicates if the value of an <input>, after having been edited by the user, does not conform to the constraints set by the element's max attribute.
dom-validitystate-rangeoverflow.title: ValidityState: rangeOverflow property

dom-validitystate-rangeunderflow.name: rangeUnderflow
dom-validitystate-rangeunderflow.summary: The read-only rangeUnderflow property of a ValidityState object indicates if the value of an <input>, after having been edited by the user, does not conform to the constraints set by the element's min attribute.
dom-validitystate-rangeunderflow.title: ValidityState: rangeUnderflow property

dom-validitystate-stepmismatch.name: stepMismatch
dom-validitystate-stepmismatch.summary: The read-only stepMismatch property of a ValidityState object indicates if the value of an <input>, after having been edited by the user, does not conform to the constraints set by the element's step attribute.
dom-validitystate-stepmismatch.title: ValidityState: stepMismatch property

dom-validitystate-toolong-dev.name: tooLong
dom-validitystate-toolong-dev.summary: The read-only tooLong property of a ValidityState object indicates if the value of an <input> or <textarea>, after having been edited by the user, exceeds the maximum code-unit length established by the element's maxlength attribute.

firefox.notes: Not supported in the unlikely case of the value being initially set too long, and then changed by the user to a still incorrect state. Per caniuse.com.

dom-validitystate-toolong-dev.title: validityState: tooLong property

dom-validitystate-tooshort-dev.name: tooShort
dom-validitystate-tooshort-dev.summary: The read-only tooShort property of a ValidityState object indicates if the value of an <input>, <button>, <select>, <output>, <fieldset> or <textarea>, after having been edited by the user, is less than the minimum code-unit length established by the element's minlength attribute.
dom-validitystate-tooshort-dev.title: ValidityState: tooShort property

dom-validitystate-typemismatch.name: typeMismatch
dom-validitystate-typemismatch.summary: The read-only typeMismatch property of a ValidityState object indicates if the value of an <input>, after having been edited by the user, does not conform to the constraints set by the element's type attribute.
dom-validitystate-typemismatch.title: ValidityState: typeMismatch property

dom-validitystate-valuemissing-dev.name: valueMissing

dom-frameelement-dev.name: frameElement

dom-frames-dev.name: frames

dom-localstorage-dev.name: localStorage

handler-window-onmessage.name: message_event
handler-window-onmessage.summary: The message event is fired on a Window object when the window receives a message, for example from a call to Window.postMessage() from another browsing context.

event-online.name: online_event

handler-window-ononline.name: online_event
handler-window-ononline.summary: The online event of the Window interface is fired when the browser has gained access to the network and the value of Navigator.onLine switches to true.

event-popstate.summary: The popstate event of the Window interface is fired when the active history entry changes while the user navigates the session history. It changes the current history entry to that of the last page the user visited or, if history.pushState() has been used to add a history entry to the history stack, that history entry is used instead.

chrome.notes: Before version 34, Chrome would fire a popstate event on page load.

safari.notes: Before version 10, Safari would fire a popstate event on page load.

webview_android.notes: Before version 37, WebView would fire a popstate event on page load.

edge_blink.notes: Before version 34, Chrome would fire a popstate event on page load.

event-popstate.title: Window: popstate event

It changes the current history entry to that of the last page the user visited or, if history.pushState() has been used to add a history entry to the history stack, that history entry is used instead.

chrome.notes: Before version 34, Chrome would fire a popstate event on page load.

safari.notes: Before version 10, Safari would fire a popstate event on page load.

webview_android.notes: Before version 37, WebView would fire a popstate event on page load.

dom-window-postmessage-options-dev.name: postMessage
dom-window-postmessage-options-dev.summary: The window.postMessage() method safely enables cross-origin communication between Window objects; e.g., between a page and a pop-up that it spawned, or between a page and an iframe embedded within it.

notes: Firefox 8 and up supports sending File and FileList objects between windows. This is only allowed if the recipient's principal is contained within the sender's principal for security reasons.

Before Firefox 6, the message parameter must be a string. Since Firefox 6, the message parameter is serialized using the structured clone algorithm. This means you can pass a broad variety of data objects safely to the destination window without having to serialize them yourself.

ie.notes: IE10 had an important limitation: see this article for details.
Support only for <frame> and <iframe>.

dom-animationframeprovider-requestanimat.summary: The window.requestAnimationFrame() method tells the browser that you wish to perform an animation and requests that the browser calls a specified function to update an animation right before the next repaint. The method takes a callback as an argument to be invoked before the repaint.

firefox.notes: Callback parameter is a DOMHighResTimestamp. This means ten microsecond precision and zero time as performance.now().
Callback parameter is a DOMTimestamp. This means millisecond precision and zero time as Date.now().
Could be called with no input parameters.

dom-self-dev.name: self
dom-self-dev.summary: The Window.self read-only property returns the window itself, as a WindowProxy. It can be used with dot notation on a window object (that is, window.self) or standalone (self). The advantage of the standalone notation is that a similar notation exists for non-window contexts, such as in Web Workers. By using self, you can refer to the global scope in a way that will work not only in a window context (self will resolve to window.self) but also in a worker context (self will then resolve to WorkerGlobalScope.self).

dom-sessionstorage-dev.name: sessionStorage
dom-sessionstorage-dev.summary: The read-only sessionStorage property accesses a session Storage object for the current origin. sessionStorage is similar to localStorage; the difference is that while data in localStorage doesn't expire, data in sessionStorage is cleared when the page session ends.
